WEBVTT

1
00:00:27.480 --> 00:00:29.914
I love this place. I really do.

2
00:00:30.200 --> 00:00:33.078
It's a great place to hang your hat.
or lift your leg.

3
00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:34.509
It's so me!

4
00:00:34.800 --> 00:00:38.395
The bay breeze. the Golden Gate.
Fisherman's Wharf...

5
00:00:38.680 --> 00:00:39.795
...the females...

6
00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:44.072
Yeah. don't even get this dog
started on the females!

7
00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:46.954
Just something about the way
a girl sips her latte...

8
00:00:47.120 --> 00:00:49.793
...that gets me
a little hot under the collar.

9
00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:53.153
But enough about me.
Let's talk about why we're here:

10
00:00:53.720 --> 00:00:55.039
...the Dolittles.

11
00:00:55.440 --> 00:00:58.557
Maya Dolittle is not the doctor.
the daughter.

12
00:00:59.560 --> 00:01:01.152
You see. she's adjusting.

13
00:01:01.320 --> 00:01:03.231
She's going through
that weird period...

14
00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:05.994
...that every
one-in-a-trillion girls go through.

15
00:01:06.320 --> 00:01:08.356
It's not every day
a young woman wakes up...

16
00:01:08.520 --> 00:01:11.671
...and realizes she can talk
to animals. and we can talk to her.

17
00:01:13.320 --> 00:01:15.675
I thought you said
you actually had your license?

18
00:01:15.840 --> 00:01:17.910
Just chill out!
Everything's under control now.

19
00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:20.230
Just don't kill me
before the party tomorrow night!

20
00:01:20.400 --> 00:01:22.675
I burned the dopest CD
for everyone to freak to.

21
00:01:24.200 --> 00:01:26.589
- Oh. my God. I just had
the best idea. - What?

22
00:01:26.760 --> 00:01:29.354
You should totally have a birthday
party at the end of summer...

23
00:01:29.520 --> 00:01:30.953
...and we'll make sure
it's off the chain...

24
00:01:31.120 --> 00:01:33.031
...and then you'll be part
of the "A" list with me!

25
00:01:33.200 --> 00:01:36.556
I don't know how to tell you this.
but you've been more of a "B" lately.

26
00:01:37.400 --> 00:01:39.277
Which would make me a "C" at best.

27
00:01:39.720 --> 00:01:41.676
I am so hating
my social status right now!

28
00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:44.638
What do you expect? Running around
talking to animals all the time?

29
00:01:44.800 --> 00:01:45.755
I told you a million times:

30
00:01:45.920 --> 00:01:47.911
...I don't talk to them.
they keep talking to me!

31
00:01:48.080 --> 00:01:49.513
- Maya. watch out!
- Oh. no!

32
00:01:55.160 --> 00:01:56.309
What are you doing?!

33
00:01:57.240 --> 00:02:00.312
What did you do that for. lady?
I was gonna pee on that!

34
00:02:02.920 --> 00:02:03.909
How bad?

35
00:02:05.920 --> 00:02:07.069
Oh. no!

36
00:02:07.240 --> 00:02:08.514
You drive like a freaking animal!

37
00:02:08.680 --> 00:02:11.240
Are you nuts?
You can get people killed like that!

38
00:02:11.400 --> 00:02:13.550
Don't tell it to me.
tell it to the pig!

39
00:02:23.320 --> 00:02:25.595
So I talked to Heather.
who text-messaged Mandy...

40
00:02:25.760 --> 00:02:27.796
...who IM'd Christy.
who two-way'd with Tammy...

41
00:02:27.960 --> 00:02:30.872
...and the bottom line is we're both
invited to the party tonight!

42
00:02:31.040 --> 00:02:32.553
Oh. my. God! You're the best!

43
00:02:32.800 --> 00:02:35.553
So then I invited them
to your party at the end of summer.

44
00:02:36.080 --> 00:02:38.719
- You did what?
- I didn't want to be rude.

45
00:02:39.120 --> 00:02:40.075
Rude?

46
00:02:40.240 --> 00:02:43.596
Rude is inviting somebody to a party
that doesn't even exist yet!

47
00:02:43.760 --> 00:02:45.478
Look. do you want to be in or not?

48
00:02:45.640 --> 00:02:47.119
So... Maya.

49
00:02:47.280 --> 00:02:49.919
I hear you're having
a birthday party this summer...

50
00:02:50.440 --> 00:02:53.637
Yes. and it would be so cool
if all of you guys came. I mean...

51
00:02:53.800 --> 00:02:55.791
I assume you're having it
somewhere worthwhile?

52
00:02:55.960 --> 00:02:59.430
- I don't really know yet. but...
- It's on a boat.

53
00:02:59.640 --> 00:03:00.993
Like. on a rowboat?

54
00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:05.478
Actually. it's on a huge.
P. Diddy-like boat.

55
00:03:06.920 --> 00:03:10.549
How MTV of you!
We'll think about it.

56
00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:16.231
A birthday party.
That is so freshman year!

57
00:03:17.200 --> 00:03:19.156
They're so coming. I can feel it!

58
00:03:19.920 --> 00:03:23.230
You ready? We've got to go.
We got to help set up for Senior Day.

59
00:03:24.080 --> 00:03:25.149
20 minutes. people!

60
00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:28.516
Hey. dude!
You rolling to the jump off tonight?

61
00:03:28.680 --> 00:03:30.557
- It's gonna be off the hook.
- Hi. Carl.

62
00:03:33.960 --> 00:03:35.757
He nodded at me. did you see that?

63
00:03:35.920 --> 00:03:37.831
Keep it up.
and he might actually talk to you.

64
00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:39.433
Nice shot.
you freaking moron!

65
00:03:39.600 --> 00:03:40.999
Give the bird a break. dude!

66
00:03:41.160 --> 00:03:42.798
What's with you
and that dumb thing?

67
00:03:42.960 --> 00:03:45.474
I just feel bad for him.
being locked up in a cage...

68
00:03:45.640 --> 00:03:47.756
How do you feel so bad for him?

69
00:03:48.160 --> 00:03:51.596
How? The only person who has
the combination is Principal Thomas.

70
00:03:51.760 --> 00:03:53.716
Aw. jeez. it's 8-15-27!

71
00:03:53.960 --> 00:03:57.635
Hey. guys.
maybe you should try 8-15-27.

72
00:03:58.000 --> 00:03:59.035
Great!

73
00:03:59.360 --> 00:04:02.079
The freak that talks to animals.
Wait. let me guess:

74
00:04:02.240 --> 00:04:04.037
...the hawk told you the combo?

75
00:04:04.280 --> 00:04:07.636
So. what if he did? You don't have
to be a jerk about it.

76
00:04:07.880 --> 00:04:10.599
Go ahead then. Carl.
Let the bird out. I dare you.

77
00:04:17.320 --> 00:04:19.072
Alright! Shake a tail feather!

78
00:04:19.240 --> 00:04:21.356
Oh. thanks a lot. pal.
I'll be right back.

79
00:04:22.200 --> 00:04:25.112
Ladies and gentlemen.
the hawk has left the building!

80
00:04:25.320 --> 00:04:26.833
- Sweet.
- I owe you one.

81
00:04:31.920 --> 00:04:33.956
There is Maya Dolittle!

82
00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:40.195
Anybody who is anybody
is gonna be there.

83
00:04:40.360 --> 00:04:42.669
I even heard Carl call it
"the party of the year".

84
00:04:42.840 --> 00:04:45.400
Parties? Ooh-la-la!
I love parties!

85
00:04:46.360 --> 00:04:47.509
I'm sure you do.

86
00:04:47.840 --> 00:04:50.673
- Now...
- Ooh. it's that kind of party!

87
00:04:50.840 --> 00:04:53.035
- Tell me where it hurts.
- Okay. I'm ready.

88
00:04:53.200 --> 00:04:55.794
So is the party
in the neighborhood?

89
00:05:03.520 --> 00:05:05.556
Cool! Now I can see in color!

90
00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:39.309
Oh. yes. definitely.
What do you think. Lucky?

91
00:05:39.720 --> 00:05:42.029
I was thinking something.
you know. furrier.

92
00:05:42.200 --> 00:05:44.555
I'm serious.
This party is as big as it gets.

93
00:05:44.720 --> 00:05:45.914
You look great. kid!

94
00:05:46.280 --> 00:05:47.918
We were listening to that!

95
00:05:49.080 --> 00:05:51.389
I just got off the phone
with your principal...

96
00:05:51.560 --> 00:05:53.278
...and I saw
what you did to my car.

97
00:05:53.440 --> 00:05:54.589
Smells like trouble...

98
00:05:54.760 --> 00:05:56.990
Sounds like you had
an interesting afternoon.

99
00:05:57.400 --> 00:05:59.118
Yeah. but it wasn't my fault.

100
00:05:59.280 --> 00:06:01.874
I was trying to impress Carl.
and there was this bird...

101
00:06:02.040 --> 00:06:05.157
I was 17 once. too. Maya.
I know what you're going through.

102
00:06:05.360 --> 00:06:08.158
Really?
So animals chattered at you 24-7?

103
00:06:08.320 --> 00:06:11.357
No. but I do know
what it's like to want to fit in.

104
00:06:11.520 --> 00:06:14.796
Good. Then you know why I have
to finish getting ready for the party.

105
00:06:16.520 --> 00:06:17.839
I'm sorry. sweetie...

106
00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:20.389
...but I think
you have earned yourself a night in.

107
00:06:20.560 --> 00:06:21.913
But I thought you understood!

108
00:06:22.080 --> 00:06:23.911
I've been working on this look
for hours!

109
00:06:24.080 --> 00:06:25.957
Any longer.
I would've peed on the bed.

110
00:06:26.600 --> 00:06:27.999
It's just one night.

111
00:06:28.440 --> 00:06:30.192
But why does it have to be tonight?

112
00:06:30.360 --> 00:06:33.079
"Where's Maya?".
"Oh. she's at home. grounded!"

113
00:06:33.240 --> 00:06:35.708
I might as well tell everybody
you put me in a time-out.

114
00:06:35.880 --> 00:06:37.711
I'm sure there'll be other parties.

115
00:06:44.040 --> 00:06:46.349
Lucky. I need a favor.

116
00:06:46.680 --> 00:06:49.240
Give me a bone and a belly rub.
and I'm your man.

117
00:06:52.640 --> 00:06:55.074
Look. we were lucky
even to get invited. right?

118
00:06:55.240 --> 00:06:58.277
So I think the best approach
in a case like this is just...

119
00:06:58.560 --> 00:07:01.757
...to keep a low profile.
- Definitely. low pro all the way.

120
00:07:05.320 --> 00:07:07.470
Let's get
this party started. people!

121
00:07:09.320 --> 00:07:11.709
Sorry.
I guess I got a little carried away.

122
00:07:12.600 --> 00:07:15.398
We'll be lucky if anybody
even talks to us after that!

123
00:07:16.640 --> 00:07:18.517
Speak for yourself. girlfriend!

124
00:07:28.960 --> 00:07:32.157
I just wanted to say thanks
for taking the rap for me earlier.

125
00:07:34.120 --> 00:07:37.112
Please. it was...
totally my pleasure.

126
00:07:37.640 --> 00:07:40.029
Cool. So you wanna dance?

127
00:07:41.600 --> 00:07:42.635
Come on!

128
00:07:47.640 --> 00:07:51.599
Charisse is fine. but I'm getting
really worried about Maya. John.

129
00:07:53.160 --> 00:07:56.197
I know you had trouble at first.
but you were a grown man.

130
00:07:56.640 --> 00:07:59.393
Maya's a 17-year-old girl
trying to figure life out.

131
00:08:08.040 --> 00:08:10.600
You know what?
I think I might have an idea.

132
00:08:10.760 --> 00:08:12.751
I'm gonna talk to her
about it right now.

133
00:08:18.400 --> 00:08:20.038
Maya. come down!

134
00:08:20.680 --> 00:08:23.877
Hey. Maya. if you won't sing.
at least come down and dance.

135
00:08:24.040 --> 00:08:25.837
Viv! Low pro. remember?

136
00:08:26.040 --> 00:08:28.759
Oh. forget that!
You're the best dancer here.

137
00:08:29.200 --> 00:08:30.394
Step up. girl!

138
00:08:31.440 --> 00:08:32.839
Come on. Maya. let's go!

139
00:08:47.600 --> 00:08:50.160
What a doofus. and it's her wig!

140
00:08:56.400 --> 00:08:57.355
Hey. girl!

141
00:08:57.520 --> 00:08:59.909
- Is that Carl and Maya Dolittle?
- Sure. he is.

142
00:09:00.200 --> 00:09:01.758
What are you doing with her?

143
00:09:02.120 --> 00:09:03.109
Girl. I'm grooving!

144
00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:05.672
He must be out of his mind!

145
00:09:08.280 --> 00:09:10.191
Hey. Justin.
turn around. check her out!

146
00:09:11.560 --> 00:09:12.788
That dance is sick!

147
00:09:17.160 --> 00:09:18.434
These moves are tight!

148
00:09:25.680 --> 00:09:26.715
She's pretty good!

149
00:09:27.320 --> 00:09:28.958
I told you. girl!

150
00:09:36.920 --> 00:09:39.753
Dr. Maya!
My butt is ready to rock and roll!

151
00:09:39.920 --> 00:09:41.797
Let's get this party started.
people!

152
00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:50.353
Bombs away!

153
00:09:50.800 --> 00:09:52.552
- What the...?
- Fire in the hole!

154
00:09:54.320 --> 00:09:57.596
- Look out below!
- Is it hailing? - I'm so bad!

155
00:09:58.440 --> 00:10:00.556
Oh. no!
What is he doing here?

156
00:10:00.840 --> 00:10:03.673
I'm popping. I'm locking.
I'm popping. I'm locking.

157
00:10:07.520 --> 00:10:09.636
Go away! Get out of here! Shoo!

158
00:10:12.440 --> 00:10:14.112
It's time to get my freak on.

159
00:10:14.280 --> 00:10:17.875
Why are you doing this to me?
You'll ruin everything. Leave me alone!

160
00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:20.955
What?

161
00:10:25.840 --> 00:10:27.353
We were just following you.

162
00:10:32.480 --> 00:10:34.789
Here I come.
Monkey on the move!

163
00:10:36.200 --> 00:10:37.838
Time to meet some ladies!

164
00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:42.197
This way to the bar. girls!
It's ladies night!

165
00:10:42.400 --> 00:10:43.958
Is that what I think it is?

166
00:10:44.400 --> 00:10:46.470
Check it out!
It's imported from France.

167
00:10:46.640 --> 00:10:49.518
- You spiked the punch?
- Don't worry. it's good stuff.

168
00:10:50.320 --> 00:10:54.950
- Wait! Is Maya talking to it?
- Oh. no. - Who brought her anyway?

169
00:10:56.080 --> 00:10:57.593
Has anyone seen my CD?

170
00:10:58.440 --> 00:11:00.078
Au revoir. party poopers!

171
00:11:01.560 --> 00:11:03.278
Come on. Carl. let's dance.

172
00:11:09.840 --> 00:11:12.035
Look. just leave now.
and I won't tell...

173
00:11:12.680 --> 00:11:13.749
Oh. no. where'd you go?

174
00:11:13.920 --> 00:11:19.040
#Allons. enfants de la patrie.
le jour de gloire est arrive! #

175
00:11:19.960 --> 00:11:21.439
The monkey gave it to you...

176
00:11:21.800 --> 00:11:24.268
You really expect me
to believe that?

177
00:11:24.440 --> 00:11:27.512
The monkey from dad's clinic
followed me to the party. and...

178
00:11:27.680 --> 00:11:30.035
Oh. the party
that you snuck out to attend?

179
00:11:30.840 --> 00:11:33.035
Well. yeah.
but it wasn't my fault!

180
00:11:33.200 --> 00:11:35.760
- Then whose fault is it?
- This ought to be good.

181
00:11:35.920 --> 00:11:37.797
I told you.
it was the monkey's.

182
00:11:38.040 --> 00:11:40.429
Oh. the monkey. the hawk. the dog!

183
00:11:40.760 --> 00:11:42.910
The dog?
I wasn't even there! The dog...

184
00:11:43.080 --> 00:11:44.433
God. do you ever shut up?

185
00:11:44.600 --> 00:11:46.716
Don't hate the player. girl.
hate the game!

186
00:11:46.880 --> 00:11:48.279
You see. that's the problem:

187
00:11:48.440 --> 00:11:51.238
...l'm always talking to animals. Mom.
I need them to stop.

188
00:11:51.400 --> 00:11:53.038
No. you need to stop.

189
00:11:53.520 --> 00:11:56.239
I think maybe you need
to start thinking seriously...

190
00:11:56.400 --> 00:11:57.594
...about who you really are...

191
00:11:57.760 --> 00:11:59.990
...and what your future
has in store for you.

192
00:12:00.520 --> 00:12:01.475
Okay. well...

193
00:12:01.640 --> 00:12:04.313
I guess I can take a couple
of weeks off from the clinic...

194
00:12:04.480 --> 00:12:05.913
...just to get my head together.

195
00:12:06.080 --> 00:12:08.753
Maybe go down to the beach.
and do some shopping with Viv.

196
00:12:08.920 --> 00:12:10.433
The beach? I could use a tan.

197
00:12:10.600 --> 00:12:13.558
I'm talking
about a complete break...

198
00:12:13.760 --> 00:12:15.432
...a total change of scenery.

199
00:12:15.680 --> 00:12:18.035
There's this camp.
a ranch. actually...

200
00:12:18.280 --> 00:12:21.113
...that I went to when I was younger.
- Wait! A ranch?

201
00:12:21.480 --> 00:12:23.038
Yeah. that's a good one. Mom...

202
00:12:23.200 --> 00:12:25.919
...but you and I both know
I'm not a ranch kind of girl.

203
00:12:29.440 --> 00:12:32.193
I think this could be
a really good thing for you.

204
00:12:32.360 --> 00:12:33.554
Mom. you were not me!

205
00:12:35.400 --> 00:12:38.198
Oh. God. Mom!
You're sending me away?

206
00:12:38.400 --> 00:12:40.914
To a ranch. with animals?
What are you thinking?

207
00:12:41.080 --> 00:12:42.433
Maya. you love animals.

208
00:12:42.600 --> 00:12:44.556
Okay. Mom. just listen to me
for one second.

209
00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:46.638
I was almost "B" crowd once...

210
00:12:46.800 --> 00:12:49.712
...then I start talking to animals.
and I went straight to a "C".

211
00:12:49.880 --> 00:12:52.155
Now I'd just be happy
being back to "B" minus...

212
00:12:52.320 --> 00:12:54.709
...like the swim team people.
- Or the chess club even.

213
00:12:54.880 --> 00:12:57.348
I'm sorry. sweetie.
I'm trying to help you.

214
00:12:57.520 --> 00:13:00.034
But you're punishing me
for something I can't control.

215
00:13:00.200 --> 00:13:01.474
I'm not punishing you.

216
00:13:02.320 --> 00:13:05.198
You have a gift.
and you need to learn to accept it.

217
00:13:05.440 --> 00:13:08.750
I'd rather return it.
I want to talk to daddy.

218
00:13:08.920 --> 00:13:11.195
I already did.
He thinks it's a great idea.

219
00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:16.195
Well. you'd better get some sleep.
because the bus leaves at noon.

220
00:13:16.440 --> 00:13:20.797
- Wait. I'm leaving tomorrow?
- Durango is a great place.

221
00:13:20.960 --> 00:13:22.678
You're going to thank me one day.

222
00:13:22.840 --> 00:13:26.549
No. I won't!
Mom. I just want to be normal!

223
00:13:29.760 --> 00:13:31.671
I wish I wasn't a Dolittle...

224
00:13:32.560 --> 00:13:34.790
Mom. I'm serious! I'm not going!

225
00:13:36.400 --> 00:13:41.110
A ranch? What would I even wear?
Oh. my God. my hair!

226
00:13:55.240 --> 00:13:57.834
I think I just went straight
from a "C" to an "F".

227
00:13:58.000 --> 00:14:00.275
"F" is good.
"F" is the new "B".

228
00:14:00.440 --> 00:14:02.829
Mom. I can't believe
I let you talk me into this!

229
00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:08.356
Just give it a chance. honey.
I promise. one day...

230
00:14:08.760 --> 00:14:11.593
Yes. I know.
one day I'll thank you.

231
00:14:11.760 --> 00:14:13.478
Just do your best
to have a good time...

232
00:14:13.640 --> 00:14:15.949
...and everything
is going to work itself out.

233
00:14:19.360 --> 00:14:20.429
Go.

234
00:14:26.640 --> 00:14:30.189
- I don't know if I can do this.
- Sure you can! Just do what I do.

235
00:14:30.360 --> 00:14:32.271
And what is that?
Drink out of the toilet bowl?

236
00:14:32.440 --> 00:14:34.874
No. I take it one day at a time.

237
00:14:35.040 --> 00:14:36.996
Yeah. thanks for the advice.
Dr. Phil!

238
00:14:37.160 --> 00:14:40.118
- Stay off my bed while I'm gone.
- Oh. you can count on me.

239
00:14:40.280 --> 00:14:41.235
Not...

240
00:14:41.640 --> 00:14:42.595
Not...

241
00:14:47.120 --> 00:14:48.997
What happened?
You miss the bus to the mall?

242
00:14:49.160 --> 00:14:51.879
Yeah. but that was only because
I was trying to figure out...

243
00:14:52.040 --> 00:14:54.873
...how much make-up we were
going to need for your makeover.

244
00:14:55.760 --> 00:14:57.876
Okay.
it's going to be like that. huh?

245
00:14:58.040 --> 00:14:59.553
Hey. you're the one
messing with me?

246
00:14:59.720 --> 00:15:03.554
Ladies. ladies! Come on. now.
Calm down! Papa's here. alright?

247
00:15:03.720 --> 00:15:05.756
We don't need to argue.
where's love?

248
00:15:05.920 --> 00:15:07.478
Sorry. dude.
Didn't mean to do that.

249
00:15:07.640 --> 00:15:10.313
- It's a big bag. isn't it?
- Yeah... it's not the only thing!

250
00:15:10.480 --> 00:15:13.950
Coming through. Excuse me.
these are big bags. Watch out.

251
00:15:15.960 --> 00:15:17.109
Oh. come on!

252
00:15:18.720 --> 00:15:21.837
- Anybody wants some Off?
- Some back off is more like it.

253
00:15:22.000 --> 00:15:25.310
- What? It's good to be prepared.
- Prepared for what? Malaria?

254
00:15:25.720 --> 00:15:27.278
Come on.
I've got donuts here.

255
00:15:27.440 --> 00:15:30.159
D-nut? D-nut?
Want a donut? D-nut?

256
00:15:31.720 --> 00:15:32.675
Ah. cool.

257
00:15:33.240 --> 00:15:35.117
- How about you? You want one?
- No.

258
00:15:35.720 --> 00:15:36.994
Whoopsie daisy.

259
00:15:40.520 --> 00:15:42.750
Five second rule's still in effect.

260
00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:45.877
This is gonna be one long summer...

261
00:15:59.560 --> 00:16:01.790
What's the matter?
You homesick already?

262
00:16:02.640 --> 00:16:04.710
What's your problem?
You don't even know me!

263
00:16:04.880 --> 00:16:07.075
No. and I don't need
to know you either. okay?

264
00:16:07.240 --> 00:16:09.595
- I can spot your type a mile away.
- Hey. hey!

265
00:16:09.760 --> 00:16:11.398
Let's play the quiet game. huh?

266
00:16:12.240 --> 00:16:14.151
Winner gets a date with yours truly?

267
00:16:15.120 --> 00:16:18.192
Shouldn't you be. like.
at fat camp or something?

268
00:16:19.600 --> 00:16:21.830
Look. my bones are large.
Alright?

269
00:16:23.600 --> 00:16:25.397
Whatever helps you sleep at night!

270
00:16:35.920 --> 00:16:37.399
Wow. this is gorgeous!

271
00:16:37.560 --> 00:16:40.757
That's Silver Spurs. another ranch.
Your ranch is over there.

272
00:16:43.560 --> 00:16:44.629
Oh. no!

273
00:16:51.520 --> 00:16:53.715
Yeah! Finally we're here!

274
00:16:54.280 --> 00:16:55.429
Excuses-moi!

275
00:16:56.720 --> 00:16:58.119
Something stinks!

276
00:16:59.640 --> 00:17:01.596
Okay. clearly.
there's been a mistake.

277
00:17:02.040 --> 00:17:04.235
I said "A list" not "hay list".

278
00:17:09.600 --> 00:17:12.717
Hello? Mom. are you there?

279
00:17:13.240 --> 00:17:15.879
- Mom. are you there? Pick up!
- Maya!

280
00:17:17.040 --> 00:17:18.553
Come on. pick up. it's me!

281
00:17:19.280 --> 00:17:22.078
Maya. I'm coming.
Just hang on. just keep yapping.

282
00:17:22.240 --> 00:17:23.389
It's awful out here...

283
00:17:23.960 --> 00:17:25.951
Call me
whenever you get this message.

284
00:17:26.440 --> 00:17:29.273
- I need you to come pick me up.
- Maya. Maya!

285
00:17:29.880 --> 00:17:31.438
Where's that freaking button?

286
00:17:31.640 --> 00:17:34.473
- I really need to learn how to read!
- Okay. bye...

287
00:17:36.480 --> 00:17:38.038
I've got to get out of here.

288
00:17:40.480 --> 00:17:43.711
- Easy! - You princess.
what are you looking at over there?

289
00:17:45.600 --> 00:17:48.672
On second thought. maybe this place
isn't so bad after all.

290
00:17:49.800 --> 00:17:52.314
That's the only smart thing
you've said all day.

291
00:17:57.680 --> 00:17:59.113
Who are you?!

292
00:18:00.440 --> 00:18:01.873
I'll be back to you later.

293
00:18:03.480 --> 00:18:06.472
- The crapper...
- Oh. I just stepped on something!

294
00:18:10.680 --> 00:18:13.877
Howdy!
Welcome to Durango. I'm Bo.

295
00:18:14.760 --> 00:18:18.116
Wow. Bo! That was amazing
what you did with that horse!

296
00:18:18.280 --> 00:18:20.999
Do you. like.
work here or something?

297
00:18:22.800 --> 00:18:25.360
I guess you can say that.
My dad owns this place.

298
00:18:25.520 --> 00:18:26.475
Cool!

299
00:18:26.680 --> 00:18:30.150
The first thing is get you guys
unpacked. and you can go ahead and...

300
00:18:30.320 --> 00:18:31.799
You have amazing eyes!

301
00:18:35.800 --> 00:18:38.792
Thank you. that's...
mighty kind of you to say that.

302
00:18:38.960 --> 00:18:41.713
Oh. no. please tell me
I didn't just say that out loud!

303
00:18:41.880 --> 00:18:44.235
Don't worry.
I won't even hold it against you.

304
00:18:44.400 --> 00:18:45.674
By the way.
I didn't catch your name.

305
00:18:45.840 --> 00:18:47.432
I'm Brooklyn. Brooklyn Webster.

306
00:18:48.280 --> 00:18:50.271
Okay. Brooklyn Webster.
How you doing?

307
00:18:50.440 --> 00:18:52.158
I'm... doing much better now!

308
00:18:52.320 --> 00:18:54.959
I'm Maya. Maya Do...

309
00:18:56.440 --> 00:18:58.874
Dolores.
Maya Dolores Hanes.

310
00:18:59.160 --> 00:19:00.388
Maya Dolores Hanes...

311
00:19:00.560 --> 00:19:02.516
That's an interesting name
right there.

312
00:19:02.680 --> 00:19:06.389
Not really. Just your simple.
Plain Jane kind of last name.

313
00:19:06.800 --> 00:19:08.518
Nothing really special about it.

314
00:19:09.000 --> 00:19:12.595
I really like those chaps on you.
Those look... fantastic!

315
00:19:12.920 --> 00:19:15.992
And I love your hat.
It makes us look like we're twins!

316
00:19:16.960 --> 00:19:18.678
They're like moths to a flame!

317
00:19:19.320 --> 00:19:21.754
You know. it's very nice
to meet both of you ladies.

318
00:19:21.920 --> 00:19:23.558
It's nice to meet all of you. guys.

319
00:19:23.720 --> 00:19:26.280
The first thing we need to do
is get everybody unpacked...

320
00:19:26.440 --> 00:19:29.000
...and get you guys all settled in.
alright? - Okay.

321
00:19:33.560 --> 00:19:34.549
Come on. everybody...

322
00:19:34.720 --> 00:19:36.358
...l'm going to show you
all to the bunkhouse...

323
00:19:36.520 --> 00:19:39.478
...and then we can all get started
on some ranching chores. - Swell!

324
00:19:43.640 --> 00:19:45.312
I want the bed with the window!

325
00:20:02.320 --> 00:20:03.878
Oh. what a dump!

326
00:20:06.040 --> 00:20:08.634
Were you expecting the Four Seasons.
or something?

327
00:20:09.200 --> 00:20:12.636
Okay. did I do something specific
or are you always such a...

328
00:20:12.840 --> 00:20:15.877
Oh. I'm sorry. did I hurt
your little Miss Priss feelings?

329
00:20:16.040 --> 00:20:18.270
No. seriously.
do you always act like this?

330
00:20:18.440 --> 00:20:20.158
Only when I see something I want.

331
00:20:23.120 --> 00:20:24.678
And right now. I want Bo.

332
00:20:25.760 --> 00:20:28.274
So you need to back off. okay?

333
00:20:29.760 --> 00:20:30.715
Thank you!

334
00:20:55.120 --> 00:20:58.032
Hey. Jud. I got those animals
loaded up and ready to go.

335
00:20:58.400 --> 00:20:59.389
Okay. Walt.

336
00:20:59.680 --> 00:21:02.592
I sure appreciate you taking
that livestock off my hands.

337
00:21:02.840 --> 00:21:04.398
That's what neighbors are for.

338
00:21:04.720 --> 00:21:06.995
Despite always whipping
your butt at the rodeo...

339
00:21:07.160 --> 00:21:10.994
...the Silver Spurs has always
considered the Durango an old friend.

340
00:21:11.840 --> 00:21:14.035
Now. if there's
anything else I can do...

341
00:21:14.480 --> 00:21:15.708
...you just let me know.

342
00:21:16.120 --> 00:21:18.634
I've always got my eyes open
for some good land.

343
00:21:18.960 --> 00:21:20.154
I'm sure you do.

344
00:21:20.760 --> 00:21:22.398
Well. Walt.
if you'll excuse me...

345
00:21:22.560 --> 00:21:24.710
...I got some new recruits up there
waiting on me.

346
00:21:24.880 --> 00:21:28.111
- You take care. Jud.
- You do the same. Walter.

347
00:21:34.720 --> 00:21:36.119
Goatsies. goatsies!

348
00:21:43.480 --> 00:21:45.198
What are you looking at.
fat boy?

349
00:21:45.720 --> 00:21:46.869
Silly pigs.

350
00:21:47.120 --> 00:21:49.111
Why. you want a piece of me.
pork chop?

351
00:21:50.360 --> 00:21:52.157
Do I look funny to you. huh?

352
00:21:55.160 --> 00:21:56.673
What? I got a boog?

353
00:21:58.280 --> 00:21:59.235
I get it?

354
00:22:00.800 --> 00:22:02.028
Gone? You hungry?

355
00:22:02.200 --> 00:22:04.191
Hey. where you going?
I ain't finished with you!

356
00:22:04.360 --> 00:22:06.316
I'll see you at the buffet table!

357
00:22:08.560 --> 00:22:11.870
Hey. gang. I'm Jud Jones.
Welcome to Durango.

358
00:22:14.160 --> 00:22:16.754
I imagine most of you
already met my son Bo. here.

359
00:22:19.240 --> 00:22:23.392
We're going to be working hard here
at Durango for the next six weeks...

360
00:22:23.560 --> 00:22:26.120
...getting you all ready
to ride in the local rodeo...

361
00:22:26.280 --> 00:22:27.872
...and anyone
that trains hard enough...

362
00:22:28.040 --> 00:22:30.474
...can take a shot
at the individual competition...

363
00:22:30.640 --> 00:22:34.269
...and who knows? You might get
to win a nice. big shiny trophy.

364
00:22:34.440 --> 00:22:37.398
- Wouldn't it be easier if we just
watched it on TV? - Shut up!

365
00:22:37.560 --> 00:22:39.790
So we're not going
to be competing as a team?

366
00:22:39.960 --> 00:22:41.916
No. son.
I'm afraid that the Durango ranch...

367
00:22:42.080 --> 00:22:44.913
...doesn't enter into the team
portion of the competition.

368
00:22:45.080 --> 00:22:46.035
How come?

369
00:22:46.200 --> 00:22:48.919
Let's say it's hard to expect
a bunch of city folk...

370
00:22:49.080 --> 00:22:51.196
...to compete
against experienced cowboys.

371
00:22:51.560 --> 00:22:54.438
- But who's ready to become
a cowboy in training? - Me!

372
00:22:55.880 --> 00:22:57.108
And they call me weird!

373
00:22:59.320 --> 00:23:02.073
Are you going to teach the bull ride?
That's the coolest.

374
00:23:03.200 --> 00:23:04.394
Come on. gang!

375
00:23:04.760 --> 00:23:07.911
The best cowboy is no match
for the right bull on a bad day.

376
00:23:08.120 --> 00:23:10.998
But... you don't expect us
to do that other stuff. right?

377
00:23:11.160 --> 00:23:12.115
Oh. no. not today.

378
00:23:12.280 --> 00:23:15.477
Today. you're going to take
yourself a nice leisurely trail ride.

379
00:23:15.640 --> 00:23:16.755
And tomorrow?

380
00:23:16.920 --> 00:23:20.799
- Tomorrow. little lady.
the real work begins. - Can't wait.

381
00:23:21.560 --> 00:23:23.471
Okay. Red.
Let's see what you got.

382
00:23:26.640 --> 00:23:27.868
Okay. I can do this.

383
00:23:29.680 --> 00:23:31.557
Man. Tyler. you are a wuss!

384
00:23:31.840 --> 00:23:34.912
Here. let me show you. guys.
how it's done. okay? Watch this.

385
00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:45.956
Let me show you how it's done.

386
00:23:48.080 --> 00:23:49.638
You could use a bath around here!

387
00:23:51.440 --> 00:23:52.759
Watch this. guys.

388
00:23:57.520 --> 00:24:00.796
One at a time!
Why do I always get the fat kid?

389
00:24:04.240 --> 00:24:06.037
Shouldn't have had
that third Snickers.

390
00:24:06.200 --> 00:24:08.430
Don't worry. kid.
She'll move when the time's right.

391
00:24:08.600 --> 00:24:10.511
Well. looks like you're up. Maya!

392
00:24:11.400 --> 00:24:14.437
What's the matter. princess?
You scared you might break a nail?

393
00:24:14.600 --> 00:24:17.319
No. I've just never done
something like this before.

394
00:24:17.480 --> 00:24:20.677
- I think I'll try it later.
- Never is more like it.

395
00:24:33.960 --> 00:24:36.793
And the princess goes down!

396
00:24:37.520 --> 00:24:39.112
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

397
00:24:39.960 --> 00:24:41.632
You've got to get on her
from this side.

398
00:24:41.800 --> 00:24:44.439
Don't worry. she's pretty old.
She doesn't move like she used to.

399
00:24:44.600 --> 00:24:45.999
Old? I got you old. buddy!

400
00:24:47.120 --> 00:24:50.271
- No. no. no! Wait!
- Oh. no. no. - No. no!

401
00:24:50.440 --> 00:24:51.634
Oh. my God!

402
00:24:52.600 --> 00:24:54.158
- Move. Bo!
- Help!

403
00:24:54.320 --> 00:24:55.514
Come on. son. move!

404
00:24:56.320 --> 00:24:58.151
I thought I was off to a bad start.

405
00:24:58.640 --> 00:24:59.595
Come on!

406
00:25:00.800 --> 00:25:03.360
Whatever's your name. stop it!
Stop it. slow down.

407
00:25:03.520 --> 00:25:05.192
- Who's the old one now. huh?
- Help me!

408
00:25:05.360 --> 00:25:08.636
Hang on. Maya!
Hold back on the race!

409
00:25:15.680 --> 00:25:16.715
You alright?

410
00:25:17.840 --> 00:25:18.795
That's good.

411
00:25:18.960 --> 00:25:21.554
Let's see if we can get you
on this thing the right way!

412
00:25:25.600 --> 00:25:28.797
There you go.
See. there? Natural born rider.

413
00:25:29.280 --> 00:25:30.793
Any day. Dolores.

414
00:25:31.040 --> 00:25:32.598
Hey. Bo. thanks...

415
00:25:33.000 --> 00:25:36.310
...and maybe later you can show me
how to do all this on my own.

416
00:25:42.760 --> 00:25:45.797
"Maybe next time you can show me
how to do it on my own."

417
00:25:46.320 --> 00:25:48.675
You don't actually think
that crap's going to work. do you?

418
00:25:48.840 --> 00:25:52.674
I'm sorry. I believe the phrase is.
"Don't hate the player. hate the game".

419
00:25:52.840 --> 00:25:55.115
Game on! You got served!

420
00:25:56.040 --> 00:25:57.029
Goodbye!

421
00:26:11.680 --> 00:26:13.955
If you think I'm dirty.
you should see my pen!

422
00:26:20.640 --> 00:26:22.915
- Hey. I sleep on my own crap!
- You shut up!

423
00:26:23.080 --> 00:26:25.230
- Have you seen Cogburn lately?
- No. you shut up!

424
00:26:25.400 --> 00:26:26.549
He's not the head of the hen house.

425
00:26:30.680 --> 00:26:32.318
Hey. pig. what are you doing?

426
00:26:36.360 --> 00:26:38.476
Alright. I got one. check this out.

427
00:26:38.760 --> 00:26:41.877
What do you call
three cows sitting in a jacuzzi?

428
00:26:42.800 --> 00:26:43.789
Stew!

429
00:26:45.040 --> 00:26:47.190
Do you animals ever stop?

430
00:26:48.840 --> 00:26:50.239
What is your problem?

431
00:26:54.280 --> 00:26:56.510
Was I talking in my sleep again?

432
00:26:57.320 --> 00:26:59.470
I tend to do that. Sorry.

433
00:27:00.120 --> 00:27:02.953
- You are such a weirdo.
- 27. 28. 29...

434
00:27:03.560 --> 00:27:04.675
Shut up!

435
00:27:04.920 --> 00:27:06.353
Hey. what comes after 29?

436
00:27:07.560 --> 00:27:08.515
I knew.

437
00:27:15.560 --> 00:27:17.232
Oh. I don't even know why I bother.

438
00:27:17.400 --> 00:27:19.595
Hey. just wake up if you want!
What do I care?

439
00:27:20.120 --> 00:27:24.159
What a joke! When is Jud going
to realize we girls have our needs?

440
00:27:24.320 --> 00:27:27.437
Would it kill the man to get
a rooster with a little chutzpah?

441
00:27:30.080 --> 00:27:32.071
Cock-a-doodle-do!
Sleeping Ugly!

442
00:27:47.280 --> 00:27:48.235
Oh. no!

443
00:27:56.600 --> 00:27:57.635
You okay?

444
00:27:58.920 --> 00:28:01.673
I guess you weren't kidding
about bright and early. huh?

445
00:28:08.120 --> 00:28:09.838
Dad likes
to get a head start on the sun.

446
00:28:10.000 --> 00:28:12.309
So I'd say you got
about 10 minutes till we get going.

447
00:28:12.960 --> 00:28:13.949
Okay.

448
00:28:16.960 --> 00:28:17.995
Alright.

449
00:28:23.200 --> 00:28:24.269
So anyways...

450
00:28:24.440 --> 00:28:27.637
...I finally realized hitchhiking
is impossible without a thumb!

451
00:28:28.160 --> 00:28:31.118
So I hopped on the back
of a pickup truck. and here I am.

452
00:28:31.960 --> 00:28:36.317
- Oh. no. No way! It can't be!
- You all be good now. you hear?

453
00:28:37.560 --> 00:28:39.949
Hey. Maya!
Look who's gone country!

454
00:28:43.120 --> 00:28:47.511
Hey. there. little fellow!
Aren't you the cutest little thing?

455
00:28:47.880 --> 00:28:50.997
What's with the baby talk. Maya?
I can hear you. remember?

456
00:28:51.160 --> 00:28:54.072
Which is why you need to get
out of here. Now. go on. scram!

457
00:28:54.240 --> 00:28:56.708
But I heard your message.
I came here to rescue you.

458
00:28:56.880 --> 00:28:58.677
I'm serious.
You cannot stay here!

459
00:28:58.840 --> 00:29:00.751
If the kids find out
I'm a Dolittle. I'm...

460
00:29:00.920 --> 00:29:02.751
But you are a Dolittle.
aren't you?

461
00:29:02.920 --> 00:29:04.319
Of course I'm a Dolittle.

462
00:29:04.480 --> 00:29:06.914
Only right now.
I'm a Dolittle who's fitting in.

463
00:29:07.320 --> 00:29:10.073
If the animals find out
I can talk to them. I'm doomed!

464
00:29:10.240 --> 00:29:11.912
Why? You love animals.

465
00:29:12.120 --> 00:29:13.872
Of course I love animals.

466
00:29:14.040 --> 00:29:16.634
It's just that if they talk to me.
I'm going to talk back...

467
00:29:16.800 --> 00:29:20.156
...and if I talk back. the kids
will think I'm some kind of freak.

468
00:29:20.720 --> 00:29:23.075
You can stay here if you want...

469
00:29:23.480 --> 00:29:25.789
...but just find something
to occupy your time.

470
00:29:25.960 --> 00:29:28.315
- Occupy my time! Copy that.
- Okay.

471
00:29:29.280 --> 00:29:32.716
This doesn't have anything to do
with the cowboy behind you. does it?

472
00:29:32.880 --> 00:29:34.199
You mean the really cute one?

473
00:29:35.120 --> 00:29:36.599
He's... behind me?

474
00:29:41.080 --> 00:29:42.035
Hey!

475
00:29:43.000 --> 00:29:44.672
Are you talking to that stray dog?

476
00:29:44.840 --> 00:29:47.559
They like it for you to talk
to them like they're people...

477
00:29:47.720 --> 00:29:49.950
...because it makes them
feel important.

478
00:29:51.600 --> 00:29:53.750
- Yeah...
- So let me get this straight.

479
00:29:53.920 --> 00:29:56.639
I come all the way here
and now you're just going to ignore me?

480
00:29:56.800 --> 00:29:57.949
But I wore a wig!

481
00:29:58.440 --> 00:30:01.830
Do you have any idea how confusing
that can be to a dog's identity?

482
00:30:03.440 --> 00:30:05.271
Go round them up.
get them together.

483
00:30:05.440 --> 00:30:08.318
Alright. Durangos!
Let's go. everybody!

484
00:30:08.720 --> 00:30:12.872
- Durangos! Let's go! On the double!
- Let's go! On the double!

485
00:30:13.040 --> 00:30:14.553
Round up! Round up!

486
00:30:14.840 --> 00:30:16.990
Okay. yesterday
you all got your feet wet.

487
00:30:17.520 --> 00:30:18.999
Today you're going swimming.

488
00:30:19.160 --> 00:30:21.116
There's a pool? Sweet!

489
00:30:21.480 --> 00:30:23.357
It's a metaphor. you moron!

490
00:30:23.960 --> 00:30:25.279
Well. like I was saying...

491
00:30:25.440 --> 00:30:27.590
...it's time to find out
what you kids are made of.

492
00:30:27.760 --> 00:30:30.274
So Bo and the boys have built
a couple of contraptions...

493
00:30:30.440 --> 00:30:32.874
...to simulate what an actual rodeo
might be like.

494
00:30:33.160 --> 00:30:35.390
So remember:
Have fun out there!

495
00:30:36.000 --> 00:30:37.752
- You got 'em. son.
- Alright. Pops.

496
00:30:37.920 --> 00:30:40.036
- Let's just head on over this way.
- Cool.

497
00:30:41.400 --> 00:30:42.879
Nice shorts. Clayton!

498
00:30:44.600 --> 00:30:46.318
What. I'm a lover.
not a fighter!

499
00:30:49.800 --> 00:30:52.598
Let's go.
Nice little brisk run here. come on!

500
00:30:55.120 --> 00:30:57.475
Left. left. left. right. left...

501
00:31:06.000 --> 00:31:08.434
Who's the one talking smack now?
Huh. fat boy?

502
00:31:08.600 --> 00:31:10.238
Come on! Nay!

503
00:31:13.760 --> 00:31:16.558
Come on! You don't really think
you can catch me. do you?

504
00:31:26.240 --> 00:31:27.673
So close. yet so fat.

505
00:31:28.080 --> 00:31:30.196
Left. left. left. right. left.

506
00:31:30.520 --> 00:31:34.991
Oh! Left. left. left. right. left.
Left. left. left. right...

507
00:31:46.560 --> 00:31:48.039
Poop it out!
Come on. poop it out!

508
00:31:48.280 --> 00:31:50.111
- Hey! - Poop it!
- That's a rooster!

509
00:31:51.840 --> 00:31:52.989
I'd wash your hands.

510
00:31:56.040 --> 00:31:58.998
- Alright. let's grub!
- Finally something I'm good at!

511
00:32:05.040 --> 00:32:07.793
Maya! Maya. over here!

512
00:32:08.520 --> 00:32:11.193
It's important. Please!

513
00:32:13.960 --> 00:32:15.188
It's better be good.

514
00:32:15.600 --> 00:32:18.990
Well. you see. the thing is this...
I...

515
00:32:19.160 --> 00:32:21.116
Oh. no. I know that face.
What did you do?

516
00:32:21.280 --> 00:32:23.396
I... may or may not
have slipped up...

517
00:32:23.600 --> 00:32:26.194
...and told one or two
of the animals who you were.

518
00:32:26.440 --> 00:32:29.159
What?
Thanks for selling me up the river!

519
00:32:29.320 --> 00:32:31.709
Hey. take it easy!
I didn't know what else to say...

520
00:32:31.880 --> 00:32:33.677
...when they asked me
what I was doing here.

521
00:32:33.880 --> 00:32:34.835
It's fine.

522
00:32:36.280 --> 00:32:38.714
Wait! You're sure
it was just one or two. right?

523
00:32:38.880 --> 00:32:40.199
Yeah. pretty sure...

524
00:32:41.160 --> 00:32:43.151
And then again
it could have been...

525
00:32:44.040 --> 00:32:45.029
...all of them.

526
00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:48.035
I think that's her.

527
00:32:48.400 --> 00:32:50.231
You are so dead when we go home!

528
00:32:51.120 --> 00:32:53.634
Hey. whatever
the man's best friend thinks. huh?

529
00:32:53.800 --> 00:32:54.755
Humans...

530
00:32:55.680 --> 00:32:58.558
- Morning. Miss Dolittle!
- Hey!

531
00:32:59.440 --> 00:33:00.429
Oh!

532
00:33:01.760 --> 00:33:05.594
I don't want to ruffle any feathers.
Miss Dolittle. but I've got a problem.

533
00:33:05.760 --> 00:33:07.591
I knew this was gonna happen.

534
00:33:08.560 --> 00:33:09.879
Hey. Maya! Excuse me. girl...

535
00:33:10.040 --> 00:33:11.758
...there's something
I need to talk to you about.

536
00:33:11.920 --> 00:33:14.150
- Something really important.
- Gracie. whatever it is...

537
00:33:14.320 --> 00:33:15.878
...l'm sure
you can work it out on your own.

538
00:33:16.040 --> 00:33:18.474
But if you don't mind.
I rather be left alone. okay?

539
00:33:21.720 --> 00:33:24.678
Hello. hello!
Okey-dokey! Lob one?

540
00:33:26.080 --> 00:33:27.718
Hey. slow down there. sexy!

541
00:33:27.880 --> 00:33:30.599
Around here. that egg
is considered a collector's item!

542
00:33:30.880 --> 00:33:33.440
- Look who it is.
- Hey. ladies. what's cracking?

543
00:33:33.640 --> 00:33:35.392
The little rooster who couldn't.

544
00:33:35.720 --> 00:33:38.678
Seriously. like low egg production
is my fault.

545
00:33:38.840 --> 00:33:41.354
You're not helping anything
by mocking me. you know?

546
00:33:41.520 --> 00:33:43.272
Talk about
a cock-a-doodle-don't!

547
00:33:46.120 --> 00:33:47.075
That's very funny!

548
00:33:48.520 --> 00:33:50.795
- Hey. watch it!
- You watch it. lady!

549
00:33:51.080 --> 00:33:53.355
I had a really bad day
so far. alright?

550
00:33:53.520 --> 00:33:55.397
But if you wanna dance.
let's dance!

551
00:33:56.160 --> 00:33:58.276
Hey! What is wrong with you?

552
00:33:58.560 --> 00:34:00.471
"Oh. be a rooster!". they say.

553
00:34:00.640 --> 00:34:02.471
"Show us what you're made of".
they say.

554
00:34:02.640 --> 00:34:04.471
They think it's easy
being the only rooster...

555
00:34:04.640 --> 00:34:06.471
...on a farm full of hens?
Well. it's not!

556
00:34:06.840 --> 00:34:09.354
I'm sorry. look...
I'm just under a lot of pressure.

557
00:34:09.520 --> 00:34:11.750
I just wish there was someone
I could talk to...

558
00:34:11.920 --> 00:34:13.797
I'm sure everything's
going to be okay.

559
00:34:13.960 --> 00:34:16.872
Hey. you just talked to me!

560
00:34:17.240 --> 00:34:19.595
You mean none
of the other animals talk to you?

561
00:34:19.760 --> 00:34:22.274
Well. I've been
in kind of a funk lately.

562
00:34:22.440 --> 00:34:24.396
I haven't been out
of the coop in days.

563
00:34:24.560 --> 00:34:27.028
Well. just give it
a little bit of time.

564
00:34:27.360 --> 00:34:29.112
I'm sure everything will work out.

565
00:34:36.560 --> 00:34:38.391
Hey. people fight.
People fight!

566
00:34:38.760 --> 00:34:40.398
Don't just stand there!
Help us!

567
00:34:44.560 --> 00:34:46.471
Give me a ten-spot
on the tough one.

568
00:34:46.720 --> 00:34:49.234
- Hey!
- What? Just playing the odds.

569
00:34:59.480 --> 00:35:02.119
Disgusting!
Go ahead! Pick on the skinny guy!

570
00:35:04.000 --> 00:35:05.558
What has gotten into you. kids?

571
00:35:05.720 --> 00:35:08.280
I was planning to sell those eggs
this afternoon!

572
00:35:08.720 --> 00:35:11.996
Come on. Pops!
They're just having a little fun.

573
00:35:18.160 --> 00:35:19.229
It's like that. huh?

574
00:35:19.400 --> 00:35:20.628
Alright. then.

575
00:35:37.440 --> 00:35:38.395
So...

576
00:35:38.960 --> 00:35:42.430
...what do you women want exactly?
I mean. a guy can do so much...

577
00:35:42.600 --> 00:35:46.309
- Sorry. Cogburn. but talking to you
earlier almost got me busted. - But...

578
00:35:46.480 --> 00:35:48.311
Now. leave me alone
before somebody sees.

579
00:35:48.480 --> 00:35:49.993
But what good is talking to animals...

580
00:35:50.160 --> 00:35:52.754
...if you can't help a brother out?!
Hey. come back!

581
00:35:53.000 --> 00:35:54.558
Hey. still ignoring me?

582
00:35:54.800 --> 00:35:55.755
What do you think?

583
00:35:55.920 --> 00:35:58.354
Sheesh!
I never knew you were such a snob!

584
00:35:58.520 --> 00:36:02.229
A snob? What?
I am so not a snob!

585
00:36:02.400 --> 00:36:05.039
I'm just doing my best
to try to fit in. that's all.

586
00:36:05.240 --> 00:36:07.595
Plus. I really think
Bo is starting to like me.

587
00:36:07.840 --> 00:36:09.990
He likes you?
Who you're pretending to be?

588
00:36:10.160 --> 00:36:12.720
Can't you see that just for once
I want to be normal?

589
00:36:12.880 --> 00:36:15.269
But you're not normal. Maya.
You're a Dolittle.

590
00:36:15.440 --> 00:36:16.919
Yeah. not out here. I'm not.

591
00:36:17.080 --> 00:36:19.913
I just hate not talking to you.
You're my best friend.

592
00:36:23.800 --> 00:36:27.190
I'm sorry. I know I shouldn't
be taking any of this out on you.

593
00:36:27.360 --> 00:36:28.793
I know you're just trying to help.

594
00:36:30.040 --> 00:36:32.110
About time you gave the dog
his due!

595
00:36:34.480 --> 00:36:37.074
And I guess it's okay
if all the animals know...

596
00:36:37.240 --> 00:36:39.754
...but we have to make sure
no people find out.

597
00:36:40.000 --> 00:36:43.117
- You think I'm going to tell them?
- If you could. yeah!

598
00:36:44.720 --> 00:36:46.517
Wait!
Where have you been all morning?

599
00:36:46.680 --> 00:36:49.877
You know.
just different things...

600
00:36:50.240 --> 00:36:51.229
I love it here...

601
00:36:51.520 --> 00:36:54.990
The wide open spaces.
and the straw...

602
00:36:55.160 --> 00:36:56.912
Yeah. you met the collie.
haven't you?

603
00:36:57.080 --> 00:36:59.674
Yeah... she is smoking!

604
00:37:10.800 --> 00:37:11.755
Come on!

605
00:37:11.920 --> 00:37:14.673
Oh. forget it. Bo!
You can't break him.

606
00:37:15.400 --> 00:37:16.913
Besides. we need the money.

607
00:37:17.080 --> 00:37:18.718
Wait.
you're gonna sell him? Why?

608
00:37:18.960 --> 00:37:22.396
Pretty as he is. he ain't no use to us
if he won't let nobody ride him.

609
00:37:27.400 --> 00:37:28.515
What's his name?

610
00:37:30.520 --> 00:37:33.193
- He doesn't have one.
- Maybe you should name him.

611
00:37:35.360 --> 00:37:37.032
I wouldn't even know where to begin.

612
00:37:37.200 --> 00:37:39.668
The name's Butch.
You must be Maya.

613
00:37:40.960 --> 00:37:42.075
How about Butch?

614
00:37:43.360 --> 00:37:44.315
Why Butch?

615
00:37:44.680 --> 00:37:48.070
My mama gave me that name.
You got a problem with that. cowboy?

616
00:37:48.760 --> 00:37:52.036
I don't know. Maybe he just...
Iooks like a Butch to me.

617
00:37:53.080 --> 00:37:55.116
Alright. Then Butch it is.

618
00:38:04.360 --> 00:38:06.396
You think
you could do something for me?

619
00:38:06.560 --> 00:38:09.870
I got this rock in my shoe.
It's been driving me nuts all day.

620
00:38:10.080 --> 00:38:11.069
I'd love to.

621
00:38:16.200 --> 00:38:17.315
Let's see.

622
00:38:19.240 --> 00:38:20.593
Come on! Up. Butch!

623
00:38:22.280 --> 00:38:25.431
Ah! Thanks. kid.
I guess I owe you one.

624
00:38:26.160 --> 00:38:27.388
No problem!

625
00:38:28.160 --> 00:38:30.390
But why won't you just
let them break you?

626
00:38:30.560 --> 00:38:32.073
I'm a stallion. sweetheart...

627
00:38:32.240 --> 00:38:34.231
...and stallions
don't break that easy.

628
00:38:34.400 --> 00:38:37.312
You know if they can't break you.
they're going to sell you.

629
00:38:37.480 --> 00:38:40.916
If they're gonna sell me anyway.
I might as well go down swinging.

630
00:38:41.600 --> 00:38:43.955
What do you mean
"if they're gonna sell you anyway"?

631
00:38:44.120 --> 00:38:45.075
Look around. kid.

632
00:38:45.240 --> 00:38:47.470
Jud's been selling off animals
for weeks.

633
00:38:47.640 --> 00:38:50.200
The place is starting to look
like a ghost town.

634
00:38:51.160 --> 00:38:53.435
- That's so sad.
- Tell me about it!

635
00:38:57.920 --> 00:38:58.875
Hey. Pops.

636
00:38:59.680 --> 00:39:01.716
Ain't that the darndest thing?
Look at that!

637
00:39:01.960 --> 00:39:03.791
The stallion
actually let her touch him.

638
00:39:03.960 --> 00:39:07.236
You went off to college for a year
and you still haven't figured out...

639
00:39:07.400 --> 00:39:09.914
...that there's more to a woman
than just a pretty smile?

640
00:39:11.760 --> 00:39:15.355
- Still learning. Pops.
- Every day. son!

641
00:39:29.200 --> 00:39:32.158
That's pretty impressive
the way you got on with Butch.

642
00:39:32.560 --> 00:39:34.596
- You have a lot of pets at home?
- Me?

643
00:39:35.160 --> 00:39:39.392
No! What would make you think that?
I mean. I love them and everything...

644
00:39:39.560 --> 00:39:43.075
...if that's what you're asking.
but I wouldn't say I was an expert.

645
00:39:46.960 --> 00:39:48.518
So what about you?

646
00:39:48.880 --> 00:39:51.155
You seem to be pretty in tune
with them yourself.

647
00:39:53.320 --> 00:39:56.392
Let's say I understand them a lot more
than I understand people.

648
00:39:56.560 --> 00:39:57.959
I mean. especially you girls.

649
00:39:58.120 --> 00:40:00.509
You never have to guess
what an animal is feeling.

650
00:40:00.680 --> 00:40:03.592
You know. I think that hay
this morning gave me the runs.

651
00:40:03.760 --> 00:40:06.035
Unfortunately.
I know exactly what you mean.

652
00:40:09.680 --> 00:40:11.989
Well... nice talking to you.

653
00:40:13.280 --> 00:40:14.235
You too.

654
00:40:20.600 --> 00:40:21.999
Look what we've got here!

655
00:40:22.240 --> 00:40:23.309
The amazing...

656
00:40:23.840 --> 00:40:26.957
...the wonderful... Durangos!

657
00:40:28.840 --> 00:40:30.637
Let's go see these little cats!

658
00:40:33.160 --> 00:40:35.151
Take a good look from over there.
Durangos.

659
00:40:35.320 --> 00:40:37.117
That's as close
as you're ever going to get...

660
00:40:37.280 --> 00:40:41.114
...'cause you're not welcome over here.
- Like we care. Little Lord Fauntleroy!

661
00:40:41.280 --> 00:40:42.474
Watch it. girl!

662
00:40:42.640 --> 00:40:44.631
What?
You better watch you're mouth...

663
00:40:44.800 --> 00:40:46.870
Hey! Look.
Knock it off. alright. guys?

664
00:40:47.320 --> 00:40:48.355
Just knock it off.

665
00:40:49.520 --> 00:40:51.829
Should probably enjoy your summer.
though. Bo.

666
00:40:52.000 --> 00:40:53.672
Looks like it's going to be your last.

667
00:40:53.840 --> 00:40:56.195
- What is that supposed to mean?
- Nothing.

668
00:40:57.920 --> 00:40:59.035
Nothing at all. man.

669
00:40:59.760 --> 00:41:02.832
- Let's just go. you all.
- That's right. tuck tail and run!

670
00:41:03.520 --> 00:41:06.318
Seems to be the only thing you
and your dad are good at teaching.

671
00:41:14.400 --> 00:41:15.879
Guess I'll see you later!

672
00:41:17.440 --> 00:41:19.795
Come on. boy! Let's get going.

673
00:41:22.440 --> 00:41:24.556
- Let's go.
- See you later. Durangos!

674
00:41:25.120 --> 00:41:27.236
Let's get out of here! Yeah!

675
00:41:40.320 --> 00:41:43.517
Cattle drive. sleep outside.
Haven't they ever heard of ticks?

676
00:41:43.920 --> 00:41:45.831
The word is that the collie's coming.

677
00:41:46.000 --> 00:41:48.230
Hey. you know me.
I love working the road.

678
00:41:52.040 --> 00:41:53.268
That's the spirit gang.

679
00:41:53.440 --> 00:41:55.715
See. the more we work together
the better we'll be.

680
00:41:58.120 --> 00:41:59.917
See. ranching's all about teamwork.

681
00:42:00.080 --> 00:42:02.150
Hear that?
Maybe us two should buddy up.

682
00:42:02.480 --> 00:42:03.629
You're not that lucky.

683
00:42:05.160 --> 00:42:06.115
Shucks!

684
00:42:06.280 --> 00:42:09.477
I left some of the army blankets
in the gear hut. I'll be back.

685
00:42:09.640 --> 00:42:12.108
- No. You stay put. I'll go get them.
- Thank you.

686
00:42:12.280 --> 00:42:13.793
Isn't that helpful of you. Maya?

687
00:42:14.080 --> 00:42:15.718
Hey. Jud. that's a safety hazard.

688
00:42:18.240 --> 00:42:19.309
Careful! My...

689
00:42:21.440 --> 00:42:23.271
This is gonna be one long ride.

690
00:42:24.840 --> 00:42:25.795
Yeah.

691
00:43:02.080 --> 00:43:04.036
I wonder why he never said anything!

692
00:43:11.920 --> 00:43:13.990
Hey. Dad!
Something's going on to you.

693
00:43:14.160 --> 00:43:16.993
Are you going to tell me
or to keep it bottled up as usual?

694
00:43:17.160 --> 00:43:18.718
I know I should've told you sooner...

695
00:43:18.880 --> 00:43:22.316
...but the bank's going to foreclose
on the place in a couple of weeks...

696
00:43:22.480 --> 00:43:24.471
...if I don't catch up on the payments.

697
00:43:24.720 --> 00:43:27.951
We'll figure out how to get the money.
We always do.

698
00:43:37.400 --> 00:43:39.118
This is the open range. gang.

699
00:43:42.000 --> 00:43:44.560
So far we've been teaching you
individual skills.

700
00:43:44.920 --> 00:43:49.038
To get out here. you all put your skills
together in what we call "team work".

701
00:43:49.880 --> 00:43:50.869
Hey. Jud!

702
00:43:51.120 --> 00:43:53.475
- You really like it out here. huh?
- I love it.

703
00:43:54.120 --> 00:43:57.032
See. Maya. it's days like this
that make me understand...

704
00:43:57.240 --> 00:44:00.596
...why the settlers moved West
and risked everything they had.

705
00:44:01.760 --> 00:44:02.875
It was their destiny.

706
00:44:03.520 --> 00:44:05.476
That's one thing
I've come to find out.

707
00:44:06.440 --> 00:44:08.237
You can't fight your destiny. Maya.

708
00:44:08.720 --> 00:44:12.235
No matter how much you think
it might cost you. You can't fight it.

709
00:44:16.400 --> 00:44:19.039
Hey. Pops!
I went all the way down to the river.

710
00:44:19.360 --> 00:44:21.237
You know over there
by Silver Spurs?

711
00:44:22.000 --> 00:44:23.911
I spotted a herd...

712
00:44:24.480 --> 00:44:26.835
...just down the way up here.
about half a mile.

713
00:44:27.000 --> 00:44:29.116
Okay.
Gang. now listen up!

714
00:44:29.280 --> 00:44:31.510
Now me and Bo will do
most of the cutting...

715
00:44:31.680 --> 00:44:35.150
...but you kids feel free to jump
in any time you want. okay? - Okay.

716
00:44:35.320 --> 00:44:37.197
- Go ahead. Bo. lead on.
- Awesome!

717
00:44:41.560 --> 00:44:42.788
Come along!

718
00:44:43.280 --> 00:44:46.238
Durango. let's go!

719
00:45:14.160 --> 00:45:16.116
I'm gonna miss
this place. too. girl!

720
00:45:18.760 --> 00:45:20.637
Come on. buddy! Let's go!

721
00:45:24.600 --> 00:45:26.670
Can I take a picture?
I want to show it to mom.

722
00:45:51.240 --> 00:45:53.549
Hey! If I get you. boy!

723
00:45:54.000 --> 00:45:55.479
You're not going to take my candy!

724
00:45:55.640 --> 00:45:57.596
Alright. stampede!

725
00:46:06.200 --> 00:46:07.349
He got him!

726
00:46:08.240 --> 00:46:09.832
Hey. get your own candy!

727
00:46:10.600 --> 00:46:13.478
Note to self:
Don't steal candy from fat kids.

728
00:46:21.800 --> 00:46:23.279
Oh. my God!

729
00:46:23.440 --> 00:46:27.194
Relax. now. sweetheart.
Nobody else move a muscle.

730
00:46:28.160 --> 00:46:29.798
Oh. my God. I'm gonna die!

731
00:46:29.960 --> 00:46:32.520
No. you're not!
Nobody's gonna die on my watch. baby.

732
00:46:32.680 --> 00:46:34.910
Besides. his bark
is a lot worse than his bite.

733
00:46:38.280 --> 00:46:39.235
What the...?

734
00:46:42.640 --> 00:46:45.916
Look at Tyler. will you?
Will you look at him?

735
00:46:47.480 --> 00:46:48.708
Way to go. boy!

736
00:46:49.320 --> 00:46:50.275
I did it!

737
00:46:58.800 --> 00:47:02.509
You ever danced with the devil
in the pale moonlight?

738
00:47:05.640 --> 00:47:07.676
Hey. who killed the lights?

739
00:47:07.840 --> 00:47:09.558
I heard they taste like chicken.

740
00:47:18.360 --> 00:47:19.429
Thank you.

741
00:47:23.400 --> 00:47:25.595
- Lucky. was that a wolf?
- Wolf. shmolf.

742
00:47:26.080 --> 00:47:27.911
I eat those chumps for breakfast.

743
00:47:28.360 --> 00:47:30.510
Care for a midnight stroll?

744
00:47:32.360 --> 00:47:34.590
Why don't I get inside here
and rescue you?

745
00:47:36.000 --> 00:47:39.834
So how do you like it?
The whole being-a-cowboy thing?

746
00:47:42.800 --> 00:47:44.631
I wouldn't know. I mean...

747
00:47:44.880 --> 00:47:47.553
...I spent the last year
as a freshman at Palo Alto.

748
00:47:48.280 --> 00:47:49.235
Really?

749
00:47:49.920 --> 00:47:52.514
Well. Palo Alto's not that far
from San Francisco.

750
00:47:54.360 --> 00:47:56.191
I've been thinking the same thing.

751
00:48:08.560 --> 00:48:10.994
You see. it's a great night.

752
00:48:12.040 --> 00:48:13.155
"Va vest".

753
00:48:17.880 --> 00:48:18.995
The best.

754
00:48:20.080 --> 00:48:21.593
That's what I meant to say.

755
00:48:23.480 --> 00:48:24.515
The best.

756
00:48:37.120 --> 00:48:40.476
A cattle drive! More like
a cattle marathon. Am I right?

757
00:48:42.920 --> 00:48:43.875
There it is!

758
00:48:45.080 --> 00:48:46.559
That's the Bekerman place.

759
00:48:47.880 --> 00:48:49.518
It's a beautiful spread. isn't it?

760
00:48:49.760 --> 00:48:51.671
I never get tired of looking at it.

761
00:48:52.160 --> 00:48:55.197
Tell me. Pops! You think they've earned
a night on the town?

762
00:49:02.600 --> 00:49:03.635
Yeah. I reckon.

763
00:49:06.520 --> 00:49:07.839
Don't fall off the horse!

764
00:49:16.840 --> 00:49:20.150
- This music's giving me a headache.
- Baby. a headache?

765
00:49:20.320 --> 00:49:22.117
I thought we were gonna
sniff each other.

766
00:49:32.720 --> 00:49:36.554
I like this place.
It's not my usual crowd but I like it.

767
00:49:36.880 --> 00:49:39.075
Oh. yeah?
So what's your usual crowd then?

768
00:49:40.000 --> 00:49:42.594
This might sound a little corny...

769
00:49:43.160 --> 00:49:45.435
...but I think
I'm just now figuring that out.

770
00:49:47.840 --> 00:49:48.875
Check it out.

771
00:49:50.360 --> 00:49:53.318
Easy. fat boy! Isn't there
some kind of weight limit here?

772
00:49:53.480 --> 00:49:54.549
You break it. you buy it.

773
00:49:54.720 --> 00:49:56.597
You aren't thinking
what I think you're thinking.

774
00:49:56.760 --> 00:49:59.752
There's a time in every man's life
when he has to put his foot down...

775
00:49:59.920 --> 00:50:01.114
...and draw a line in the sand.

776
00:50:01.280 --> 00:50:04.670
- Yeah. but does that have to be here?
- Yes. - Against them? - Yes.

777
00:50:06.800 --> 00:50:07.755
Alright.

778
00:50:08.760 --> 00:50:09.875
Light me up!

779
00:50:11.240 --> 00:50:12.753
This is gonna be good!

780
00:50:18.840 --> 00:50:20.592
Boy down!
Look at that!

781
00:50:23.920 --> 00:50:26.434
Move out of the way.
I'm gonna show you how it's done.

782
00:50:26.600 --> 00:50:27.749
Excuse me!

783
00:50:29.120 --> 00:50:30.917
Alright. kids.
Show what you get.

784
00:50:32.200 --> 00:50:35.909
Okay. Why don't I show you losers
how a real cowboy does it. alright?

785
00:50:36.120 --> 00:50:38.918
Bring it up a few notches.
let me show off.

786
00:50:49.640 --> 00:50:51.073
Take a look. Durango!

787
00:50:52.560 --> 00:50:57.350
Care to take a shot at the title?
Or are you still a has-been. Bo?

788
00:51:00.160 --> 00:51:02.594
Durangos. we leave in an hour.

789
00:51:05.760 --> 00:51:09.309
An hour? Looks like
there's trouble in paradise!

790
00:51:11.400 --> 00:51:13.789
Alright. don't forget. folks!

791
00:51:16.400 --> 00:51:17.435
Stings. huh?

792
00:51:20.640 --> 00:51:24.713
#Settle down. Cinderella.
Keep it together. #

793
00:51:24.920 --> 00:51:29.436
#Your handsome fella
will ride up sooner or later. #

794
00:51:30.400 --> 00:51:35.428
#Yeah. and take you away.
yeah! #

795
00:51:35.680 --> 00:51:40.800
#Settle down. Cinderella.
love's gonna find you some day. #

796
00:51:47.560 --> 00:51:51.553
Cinderella. my butt!
More like the evil step-sister!

797
00:51:52.360 --> 00:51:56.638
What about a tough act to follow!
Give it up for Kiki!

798
00:51:57.480 --> 00:51:58.515
Alright!

799
00:52:00.320 --> 00:52:01.912
Guys. somebody's got to step up.

800
00:52:02.120 --> 00:52:03.872
We can't let them beat us
in everything.

801
00:52:04.040 --> 00:52:06.713
Hey. don't look at me. alright?
I already took my stand.

802
00:52:07.000 --> 00:52:08.877
(The freak that talks to animals.)

803
00:52:09.040 --> 00:52:11.759
(You need to start thinking
about who you really are.)

804
00:52:11.920 --> 00:52:13.558
(You can't fight your destiny.)

805
00:52:17.120 --> 00:52:18.269
Alright!

806
00:52:23.240 --> 00:52:25.037
Now hold your horses. everyone!

807
00:52:25.320 --> 00:52:29.233
Looks like we got
a last minute addition from Durango!

808
00:52:29.520 --> 00:52:31.511
Sure hope
she sings better than I ride!

809
00:52:31.680 --> 00:52:33.352
- Not the only one.
- Hi. everybody.

810
00:52:33.520 --> 00:52:35.272
I know you guys heard of hip-hop...

811
00:52:35.440 --> 00:52:38.591
...but this is a little something
I like to call "hick-hop".

812
00:52:39.800 --> 00:52:40.869
Check it out!

813
00:52:43.760 --> 00:52:46.035
#Sometimes my nails
match my lips and... #

814
00:52:46.240 --> 00:52:48.276
#... my jeans hug my hips. #

815
00:52:48.520 --> 00:52:53.275
#I don't feel like
doing that right now. Listen! #

816
00:52:53.440 --> 00:52:55.874
#He's on his way over. #

817
00:52:56.120 --> 00:53:00.159
I hate to admit it.
but she's pretty good.

818
00:53:02.800 --> 00:53:05.553
#You better love me
when my roots are showin'... #

819
00:53:05.720 --> 00:53:08.029
#... or I'll pack up my boots.
be goin'. #

820
00:53:08.200 --> 00:53:12.796
#Bye. bye. bye. bye. bye! Hey! #

821
00:53:13.000 --> 00:53:15.514
#If it's me
that he's impressed with... #

822
00:53:15.680 --> 00:53:17.955
#... anything I might be dressed in... #

823
00:53:18.120 --> 00:53:22.432
#... ought to be just fine. #

824
00:53:22.680 --> 00:53:24.989
#If he's the one for me.
I'll know it. #

825
00:53:25.160 --> 00:53:27.515
#He better loves me
when my roots are showin'. #

826
00:53:27.680 --> 00:53:30.035
#He better loves me
when my roots are showin'. #

827
00:53:30.200 --> 00:53:32.555
#Or I'll pack up my boots
and I'll be goin'. #

828
00:53:32.720 --> 00:53:34.073
#If it's me
that he's impressed with... #

829
00:53:34.240 --> 00:53:35.309
#... anything I'm dressed with... #

830
00:53:35.480 --> 00:53:38.711
#... ought to be just fine. #

831
00:53:40.760 --> 00:53:46.437
#Ought to be just fine... #

832
00:53:47.360 --> 00:53:50.113
#He better loves me
when my roots are showin'. #

833
00:53:50.280 --> 00:53:52.589
#Or I'll pack up my boots
and I'll be goin'. #

834
00:53:52.760 --> 00:53:57.117
#Bye. bye. bye. bye. bye! Hey! #

835
00:53:57.400 --> 00:54:00.039
#If it's me
that he's impressed with... #

836
00:54:00.200 --> 00:54:02.509
#... anything I might be dressed in... #

837
00:54:02.680 --> 00:54:06.958
#... ought to be just fine. #

838
00:54:07.240 --> 00:54:12.109
#If he's the one for me.
I'll know it. I will! #

839
00:54:12.280 --> 00:54:17.149
#If he's the one for me.
I'll know it. I will! #

840
00:54:17.320 --> 00:54:19.709
#If he's the one for me.
I'll know it! #

841
00:54:19.880 --> 00:54:23.714
#Love me
when my roots are showin'. #

842
00:54:29.720 --> 00:54:33.759
Looks like we got a new champion.
Ladies and gentlemen...

843
00:54:34.080 --> 00:54:36.548
...Maya Dolores Hayes!

844
00:54:56.960 --> 00:54:58.757
I'm sorry. but you're out of time.

845
00:54:59.760 --> 00:55:03.230
You either sell the land and what's
left of the land to Silver Spurs...

846
00:55:03.400 --> 00:55:06.551
...or the bank will foreclose
and you'll end up with nothing.

847
00:55:17.080 --> 00:55:21.039
- Okay. Bo! Bring them all in.
- Let's go everybody.

848
00:55:25.280 --> 00:55:28.113
Jud. you should have been with us.
The ride was great!

849
00:55:28.280 --> 00:55:31.113
Oh. that's good!
That's really good!

850
00:55:34.840 --> 00:55:38.230
There's no easy way to say this.
so I'm going ahead and get it over with.

851
00:55:39.920 --> 00:55:42.354
Looks like I'm going
to have to let the ranch go.

852
00:55:42.520 --> 00:55:44.192
- What?
- Got to let it go.

853
00:55:44.440 --> 00:55:48.035
- You're kidding. right?
- I'm afraid not. Brooklyn.

854
00:55:56.800 --> 00:55:57.915
I'm sorry.

855
00:56:02.080 --> 00:56:04.719
This blows. I don't want to leave.

856
00:56:05.360 --> 00:56:08.033
I know. I wish
there was something we could do.

857
00:56:11.080 --> 00:56:12.752
Let's just get some grub. guys.

858
00:56:13.160 --> 00:56:14.991
I can't believe I'm saying this...

859
00:56:15.560 --> 00:56:17.039
...but I'm not even hungry.

860
00:56:37.000 --> 00:56:38.353
Excuse me. Maya.

861
00:56:41.840 --> 00:56:45.958
Sorry to wake you. but your presence
has been requested in the barn.

862
00:57:01.760 --> 00:57:03.591
Whatever it is. make it quick.

863
00:57:04.160 --> 00:57:06.435
I don't want
anyone to see me out here.

864
00:57:12.640 --> 00:57:16.997
You're the only one who can help us.
Maya. You are our only hope.

865
00:57:17.640 --> 00:57:19.551
I don't know what to tell you. guys.

866
00:57:19.960 --> 00:57:22.155
I can't stop Jud
from selling the ranch.

867
00:57:23.080 --> 00:57:25.833
I wish I could.
but there's nothing I can do.

868
00:57:26.080 --> 00:57:29.993
Maybe the other kids would help
if you just tell them who you are.

869
00:57:30.320 --> 00:57:32.151
I can't just announce to everybody...

870
00:57:32.320 --> 00:57:34.675
...that the animals asked me
to save the ranch.

871
00:57:35.320 --> 00:57:36.594
They'll think I'm crazy.

872
00:57:36.880 --> 00:57:39.189
Don't you mean
"Bo will think you're crazy"?

873
00:57:40.600 --> 00:57:41.555
No.

874
00:57:42.760 --> 00:57:43.909
Yeah...

875
00:57:46.200 --> 00:57:47.952
Look. you guys. I can't lose him.

876
00:57:48.120 --> 00:57:51.954
You're not losing anybody.
You're a Dolittle. They'll understand.

877
00:57:52.120 --> 00:57:54.634
That's the problem. Butch:
They won't understand.

878
00:57:55.560 --> 00:57:56.834
Other kids never do.

879
00:57:57.080 --> 00:58:01.437
- We can't do this without you.
You're our voice. Maya. - Sorry.

880
00:58:03.800 --> 00:58:06.951
Dolittle?
More like "Donothing".

881
00:58:10.160 --> 00:58:12.879
Maya.
you've got to tell them the truth.

882
00:58:49.520 --> 00:58:50.589
Woah. Red.

883
00:58:51.600 --> 00:58:53.352
It's getting to be about that time.

884
00:58:54.760 --> 00:58:58.275
Even though we weren't able
to finish the summer up properly...

885
00:58:58.440 --> 00:59:01.876
...I want everyone of you knows
that I believe in everyone of you.

886
00:59:02.200 --> 00:59:03.952
And you all might be city folk...

887
00:59:04.520 --> 00:59:07.671
...but you've got a lot of talent.
and you've got a lot of heart.

888
00:59:07.840 --> 00:59:10.559
That's not too easy to find
in folks these days.

889
00:59:12.200 --> 00:59:13.792
You all take care!

890
00:59:15.040 --> 00:59:16.598
- We'll see you. Red.
- Yeah.

891
00:59:16.760 --> 00:59:19.672
- We'll see you. Big Fella.
- Yeah. - Lay off the burgers here!

892
00:59:21.040 --> 00:59:23.793
Thank you so much.
I had so much fun.

893
00:59:24.040 --> 00:59:25.598
- God bless you.
- Thanks.

894
00:59:25.880 --> 00:59:28.872
- I'm so sorry. Jud.
- Don't you worry. sweetie-pie.

895
00:59:30.400 --> 00:59:31.674
We'll be just fine.

896
00:59:33.520 --> 00:59:34.794
Drive careful. son.

897
00:59:45.680 --> 00:59:47.113
Shotgun. I called it.

898
00:59:57.080 --> 01:00:01.517
Man. poor Jud... Did you see the look
on his face when we drove off?

899
01:00:01.840 --> 01:00:02.795
Yeah.

900
01:00:04.360 --> 01:00:06.715
I just wish there was something
we could have done.

901
01:00:06.880 --> 01:00:10.350
Man. this sucks! You guys are like
the coolest friends I've ever had.

902
01:00:10.520 --> 01:00:12.351
"Coolest"? Or "only"?

903
01:00:24.200 --> 01:00:25.952
- What?
- You know what.

904
01:00:26.200 --> 01:00:29.033
It's time. Maya. Time for you
to be a Dolittle again.

905
01:00:29.280 --> 01:00:32.317
I know I'm just a dog.
but if they really are your friends...

906
01:00:32.480 --> 01:00:33.913
...and if Bo really cares about you...

907
01:00:34.080 --> 01:00:35.957
...they'll accept you.
no matter who you are.

908
01:00:36.120 --> 01:00:38.350
But only
if you accept yourself first!

909
01:00:53.480 --> 01:00:54.754
We need to stop the bus.

910
01:00:55.600 --> 01:00:56.635
Why?

911
01:00:57.440 --> 01:00:59.556
Because I know
how we can save the ranch.

912
01:01:00.120 --> 01:01:01.394
This ought to be good.

913
01:01:10.480 --> 01:01:12.835
We enter the rodeo this weekend.
as a team...

914
01:01:13.320 --> 01:01:15.197
...and win the 50.000 dollar prize.

915
01:01:18.640 --> 01:01:22.394
Think about it! Clayton has already
proved that he can wrangle a steer...

916
01:01:22.560 --> 01:01:24.949
...and Tyler has become a pro
at the rope. now.

917
01:01:25.400 --> 01:01:27.755
And Brooklyn can ride circles
around anybody.

918
01:01:28.200 --> 01:01:31.112
Yeah. but what about the bull ride?
Who's gonna do that?

919
01:01:35.880 --> 01:01:39.190
I saw all your trophies when I got
the blankets in the hood.

920
01:01:39.520 --> 01:01:41.875
You were the best bull rider
in the whole state.

921
01:01:42.040 --> 01:01:44.713
Maya. it's too little too late.
Even if I did ride...

922
01:01:44.880 --> 01:01:47.792
...the rodeo's this weekend.
We'd never be ready in time.

923
01:01:48.640 --> 01:01:51.313
What if I told you
we also had a secret weapon...

924
01:01:51.480 --> 01:01:54.517
...something that no other ranch has.
not even Silver Spurs.

925
01:01:54.800 --> 01:01:55.755
What would that be?

926
01:01:57.040 --> 01:01:57.995
Me.

927
01:01:58.800 --> 01:02:03.476
No offense. but I didn't see you
do anything special except sing.

928
01:02:05.040 --> 01:02:07.679
My real name
isn't Maya Dolores Hanes.

929
01:02:10.160 --> 01:02:12.310
It's Maya Dolittle and...

930
01:02:13.600 --> 01:02:16.160
...I can talk to animals.

931
01:02:17.680 --> 01:02:20.194
Right. and I'm the poster boy
for Jenny Craig!

932
01:02:20.560 --> 01:02:23.279
- I'm serious. Clayton.
- I knew you looked familiar.

933
01:02:23.440 --> 01:02:25.476
I see your dad
on the news all the time.

934
01:02:25.640 --> 01:02:28.108
Yes. And I'm sorry
I lied to you. guys...

935
01:02:28.280 --> 01:02:31.716
...but I didn't want you to look at me
like I was freak or something.

936
01:02:32.320 --> 01:02:34.436
The point is
all the animals came to me...

937
01:02:34.600 --> 01:02:36.716
...and they really
don't wanna be sold.

938
01:02:36.960 --> 01:02:38.791
They love Durango as much as we do.

939
01:02:39.160 --> 01:02:42.550
And the way I see it. they can
tell us what we need to do to win.

940
01:02:43.080 --> 01:02:45.469
Do you know what?
That might actually work.

941
01:02:50.480 --> 01:02:53.392
What the heck? I'm in.
If it's going to help Jud out...

942
01:02:54.280 --> 01:02:55.599
...l'm with you. girl.

943
01:02:55.840 --> 01:02:57.956
Time to cowboy up. everybody!

944
01:03:05.720 --> 01:03:07.199
So what do you think. Bo?

945
01:03:14.640 --> 01:03:16.596
Look. I'm sorry I lied to you...

946
01:03:17.320 --> 01:03:18.878
...but it was because I liked you.

947
01:03:19.040 --> 01:03:22.555
Out of all the time we spent together.
the things we said to one another...

948
01:03:22.960 --> 01:03:26.157
...you wait until now to tell me
that you can talk to animals.

949
01:03:26.600 --> 01:03:28.875
Back home
I was considered a weirdo.

950
01:03:29.520 --> 01:03:31.238
That's why
my mom sent me here...

951
01:03:31.920 --> 01:03:33.638
...so I could make a fresh start.

952
01:03:34.160 --> 01:03:37.470
It may have taken me a little longer
than it should have. but...

953
01:03:37.640 --> 01:03:42.156
Wait. If you let me finish.
there's something I have to ask you.

954
01:03:44.120 --> 01:03:46.111
Do you have any idea
how cool that is?

955
01:03:46.280 --> 01:03:47.872
Look. I'll understand if you...

956
01:03:49.280 --> 01:03:50.998
Wait! What did you say?

957
01:03:51.200 --> 01:03:54.237
I said that's about the coolest thing
that I've ever heard.

958
01:03:54.920 --> 01:03:59.630
I've practically spent my whole life
wishing that I could talk to animals...

959
01:04:00.000 --> 01:04:01.149
...and you can!

960
01:04:02.200 --> 01:04:03.838
I hate to say I told you so.

961
01:04:04.680 --> 01:04:06.989
So wait! You're not mad?

962
01:04:07.320 --> 01:04:10.710
Mad? No!
Sweetie. come here.

963
01:04:13.280 --> 01:04:14.713
Now why would I be mad?

964
01:04:14.880 --> 01:04:17.155
Other than the fact
that I have to ride...

965
01:04:17.320 --> 01:04:19.880
...a 2000 pound animal
that wants to kill me...

966
01:04:21.960 --> 01:04:25.953
I mean. no. I'm not.
I'm cool.

967
01:04:27.680 --> 01:04:31.195
- Come on. we've got a meeting
that we've got to interrupt. - Cool.

968
01:04:47.440 --> 01:04:49.112
All I need is a signature. Jud.

969
01:04:57.800 --> 01:04:58.915
Here you go. Jud!

970
01:04:59.520 --> 01:05:01.829
You can keep it. if you like.
as a souvenir.

971
01:05:15.920 --> 01:05:18.992
Dad. wait! Don't sign anything!

972
01:05:19.240 --> 01:05:22.391
Hold on. tiger. Your daddy's
just about to finish some business.

973
01:05:22.560 --> 01:05:24.278
No. you hold your horses. Walter.

974
01:05:24.440 --> 01:05:26.510
Sounds like my son
needs to speak to me.

975
01:05:26.760 --> 01:05:29.115
What's going on?
What you all two doing here?

976
01:05:29.520 --> 01:05:30.999
What brings you all over here?

977
01:05:32.560 --> 01:05:33.675
Speak up!

978
01:05:34.840 --> 01:05:36.558
I'm not who you think I am. Jud.

979
01:05:37.280 --> 01:05:39.430
I know just who you are.
Miss Dolittle.

980
01:05:40.440 --> 01:05:42.556
What?
You mean you knew it all this time?

981
01:05:42.720 --> 01:05:44.278
Why didn't you say anything?

982
01:05:44.680 --> 01:05:47.399
I figured you'd tell us
when you got good and ready.

983
01:05:48.240 --> 01:05:49.434
Well. I'm ready now.

984
01:05:49.880 --> 01:05:53.236
We all want to enter the rodeo
as a team and win the prize money.

985
01:05:54.120 --> 01:05:56.236
I can get
all the animals to co-operate...

986
01:05:56.520 --> 01:06:01.958
...if. of course. you don't sell them.
and you... promise to let them stay.

987
01:06:04.680 --> 01:06:08.389
Who are we going to get to ride a bull
for 8 second? Tell me that?

988
01:06:11.480 --> 01:06:13.948
Nope.
No. that is not going to happen.

989
01:06:14.120 --> 01:06:16.315
We've been over this
a hundred times before. Bo.

990
01:06:16.480 --> 01:06:19.677
The doctor said if you take one
more fall like you did last time...

991
01:06:20.360 --> 01:06:22.874
...you might never walk again.
No. sir. No.

992
01:06:23.040 --> 01:06:25.349
Not going to happen.
I'm not willing to take that risk.

993
01:06:25.520 --> 01:06:27.033
- But I am. okay?
- Bo!

994
01:06:27.280 --> 01:06:30.829
It's my life and it's my choice.
And I've made it. okay?

995
01:06:31.000 --> 01:06:33.036
I'm not letting them
take the ranch from us!

996
01:06:38.360 --> 01:06:39.395
Pops.

997
01:06:41.040 --> 01:06:42.598
I'm gonna get on that bull...

998
01:06:43.440 --> 01:06:48.150
...and I am not coming off
until that bell rings.

999
01:06:55.960 --> 01:06:57.393
I see the gang's all here.

1000
01:07:03.200 --> 01:07:05.430
We can do this. Jud. Together.

1001
01:07:07.960 --> 01:07:08.995
As a team.

1002
01:07:09.520 --> 01:07:11.795
Just like you taught us
at the cattle drive.

1003
01:07:17.520 --> 01:07:21.274
What the hey! At the very least.
it'll put Walter's shorts in a bunch.

1004
01:07:22.720 --> 01:07:23.789
Oh. yes!

1005
01:07:25.640 --> 01:07:28.359
Gentlemen. it seems
there's been a change of plans.

1006
01:07:29.280 --> 01:07:30.713
I'll see you at the rodeo.

1007
01:07:31.600 --> 01:07:34.478
- Looks like I got myself a team.
- But. Jud. I mean...

1008
01:07:38.040 --> 01:07:39.359
I know my way out.

1009
01:07:44.640 --> 01:07:45.595
Move it. Brooklyn!

1010
01:07:45.760 --> 01:07:47.796
The only thing is gonna hurt you
is the ground!

1011
01:07:51.120 --> 01:07:53.031
- 29 seconds.
- Is that good?

1012
01:07:53.440 --> 01:07:54.839
The winning time is 13.

1013
01:07:58.200 --> 01:08:00.634
Wait here a second. I got an idea.

1014
01:08:07.720 --> 01:08:11.235
Remember you said you owed me one?
I'm taking you up on that offer!

1015
01:08:11.400 --> 01:08:12.355
What do you mean?

1016
01:08:12.520 --> 01:08:14.750
You're the biggest
and strongest horse out here.

1017
01:08:14.920 --> 01:08:16.512
If we have any shot
of winning the rodeo...

1018
01:08:16.680 --> 01:08:19.274
...we need to let Brooklyn and Tyler
ride you in their events.

1019
01:08:19.440 --> 01:08:24.355
Me? An untamed stallion
in a real rodeo? I would be honored!

1020
01:08:33.280 --> 01:08:34.554
Lord. I hope that's mud!

1021
01:08:34.840 --> 01:08:37.673
Hey. beefcake!
When you got to go. you got to go!

1022
01:08:38.320 --> 01:08:39.275
What's he saying?

1023
01:08:39.440 --> 01:08:42.000
He's just giving
a little constructive criticism...

1024
01:08:42.160 --> 01:08:43.388
...but he says you're doing great.

1025
01:08:45.840 --> 01:08:47.558
Like that. Can you try?

1026
01:09:04.840 --> 01:09:06.990
I think you should walk like a man.

1027
01:09:07.480 --> 01:09:10.438
Well. a lot of good that does me.
I'm a rooster. remember?

1028
01:09:13.760 --> 01:09:15.239
Come on. you can do it!

1029
01:09:16.800 --> 01:09:17.835
Got it!

1030
01:09:19.120 --> 01:09:21.634
Come on. puff that chest out!
Put your shoulders back!

1031
01:09:23.840 --> 01:09:25.478
See. you know
what I'm talking about!

1032
01:09:28.160 --> 01:09:30.993
He says: "Ease up on the reins
and stake back on the saddle!".

1033
01:09:31.160 --> 01:09:33.879
Until he wants to throw. then he
should shift his weight forward.

1034
01:09:34.040 --> 01:09:36.270
Until you want to throw.
then shift your weight forward!

1035
01:09:36.440 --> 01:09:39.113
- Tell him to speed up!
- The cow wants you to speed up!

1036
01:09:39.280 --> 01:09:41.635
Forget that!
Tell the stupid calf to slow down!

1037
01:09:50.640 --> 01:09:54.030
On a personal note. I would think
twice before calling a calf stupid.

1038
01:09:54.200 --> 01:09:55.633
Can't argue with you there.

1039
01:09:56.400 --> 01:09:58.675
Left. left. left. right. left.

1040
01:09:58.840 --> 01:10:00.432
#I don't care
if you think it's true. #

1041
01:10:00.600 --> 01:10:02.079
#You'll be cowboys
when you're through! #

1042
01:10:02.240 --> 01:10:03.878
#We don't care
if you think it's true. #

1043
01:10:04.040 --> 01:10:05.632
#We'll be cowboys
when we're through! #

1044
01:10:05.800 --> 01:10:08.837
#I don't care where you've been.
Durango Ranch is going to win! #

1045
01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:12.390
#We don't care where you've been.
Durango Ranch is going to win! #

1046
01:10:16.400 --> 01:10:17.355
Like this?

1047
01:10:18.200 --> 01:10:20.350
Now you know
what I'm talking about! Let's go!

1048
01:10:20.520 --> 01:10:21.635
Okay. I'm feeling you.

1049
01:10:24.360 --> 01:10:25.315
Thanks. girlfriend!

1050
01:10:35.560 --> 01:10:37.755
That's great!

1051
01:10:43.160 --> 01:10:44.115
That's it!

1052
01:10:46.600 --> 01:10:47.749
Get you some of that!

1053
01:10:50.120 --> 01:10:52.998
- I could ride that thing.
- Yeah. if it's not moving.

1054
01:10:53.160 --> 01:10:54.115
So are you nervous?

1055
01:10:56.040 --> 01:10:58.429
A little. I guess.

1056
01:10:59.480 --> 01:11:00.549
Why? Are you?

1057
01:11:02.680 --> 01:11:03.635
Well...

1058
01:11:05.440 --> 01:11:07.749
I just don't want anybody
to get hurt out there.

1059
01:11:07.920 --> 01:11:10.798
Don't worry about it too much.
I mean those guys should be fine.

1060
01:11:10.960 --> 01:11:13.030
Yeah. well. it's not them
that I'm worried about.

1061
01:11:13.360 --> 01:11:16.079
Looks like she's about to slip him
the old tonguerooski.

1062
01:11:16.240 --> 01:11:17.195
No. I wasn't!

1063
01:11:17.600 --> 01:11:21.036
Please. I may be from right here
in the good old USA. but...

1064
01:11:21.320 --> 01:11:24.153
...I have been to France
plenty of times!

1065
01:11:24.320 --> 01:11:26.436
You are one sick puppy.
do you know that?

1066
01:11:30.520 --> 01:11:33.876
Rise and shine. Durangos.
it's winning time!

1067
01:11:35.720 --> 01:11:40.555
Good morning and welcome
to the Silver Spurs annual rodeo!

1068
01:11:41.160 --> 01:11:43.879
Today. ladies and gentlemen.
we'll have 5 teams...

1069
01:11:44.040 --> 01:11:46.873
...competing in 2 rounds
of rodeo competitions!

1070
01:11:47.240 --> 01:11:48.912
Good luck. tippers!

1071
01:11:49.080 --> 01:11:53.551
- First up. the long horn roping event!
- Come on! Untie that little doggie!

1072
01:12:00.840 --> 01:12:02.831
Oh. looks like
it's gonna be close!

1073
01:12:04.480 --> 01:12:06.755
Hey. not so tight! I bruise easy!

1074
01:12:06.920 --> 01:12:10.515
- Go. boy!
- Yes! Yes! Yes!

1075
01:12:10.840 --> 01:12:14.276
Next up. it's the big man's event:
Steer wrestling!

1076
01:12:15.480 --> 01:12:16.879
I'm going to own you. big boy!

1077
01:12:17.040 --> 01:12:20.237
I'll have you know you're looking
at a three-time state wrestling champ.

1078
01:12:21.000 --> 01:12:24.072
I'll have you know I once shoved
a whole box of Twinkies in my mouth...

1079
01:12:24.240 --> 01:12:25.195
...without swallowing them.

1080
01:12:25.360 --> 01:12:27.078
First up. Chip Woodman!

1081
01:12:35.080 --> 01:12:39.915
And that. ladies and gentlemen.
is the new record: 5.4 seconds!

1082
01:12:40.080 --> 01:12:41.035
Good luck!

1083
01:12:43.280 --> 01:12:45.077
Go back. You missed the steer man!

1084
01:12:45.240 --> 01:12:48.516
I don't know if we should give
that young man a hand or a cane!

1085
01:12:48.920 --> 01:12:50.990
It's time for some barrel racing!

1086
01:12:58.040 --> 01:12:58.995
Come on!

1087
01:13:00.440 --> 01:13:01.395
Come on. boy!

1088
01:13:04.120 --> 01:13:08.636
Coming in with a time of 16 seconds.
the Silver Spurs!

1089
01:13:09.000 --> 01:13:10.991
- Beat that!
- With pleasure!

1090
01:13:13.880 --> 01:13:16.713
Listen. Brooklyn. I know
you're not that crazy about me...

1091
01:13:16.880 --> 01:13:19.678
...and you think I'm some kind
of spoiled brat or something...

1092
01:13:20.080 --> 01:13:22.435
...but I think
the way you ride is amazing.

1093
01:13:23.000 --> 01:13:23.955
Thank you.

1094
01:13:24.120 --> 01:13:26.350
Now get out there
and kicks some butt. would you?

1095
01:13:27.080 --> 01:13:28.354
Come on. let's go!

1096
01:13:33.960 --> 01:13:35.712
Come on. Brooklyn! You can do it!

1097
01:13:37.280 --> 01:13:38.315
Go! Go!

1098
01:13:40.720 --> 01:13:42.597
- Bring it in!
- Come on!

1099
01:13:45.160 --> 01:13:47.276
13 seconds! What a great time!

1100
01:13:48.560 --> 01:13:50.312
Looks like they've got a leaner.

1101
01:13:55.600 --> 01:13:58.637
- Oh. dang it!
- What a bad break for the Durangos!

1102
01:13:58.800 --> 01:14:00.313
I shouldn't have cut it that close!

1103
01:14:02.880 --> 01:14:04.154
It's okay. You did great!

1104
01:14:04.320 --> 01:14:06.754
Despite the Silver Spurs
is having a slight lead...

1105
01:14:06.920 --> 01:14:08.797
...the championship
is still wide open...

1106
01:14:08.960 --> 01:14:12.589
...as we move into the second to last
event before everybody's favorite...

1107
01:14:12.760 --> 01:14:14.193
...the bull ride!
- Come on!

1108
01:14:15.400 --> 01:14:17.675
Durangos. everybody huddle up!
Come on. now!

1109
01:14:18.120 --> 01:14:19.473
Look. we can still win this...

1110
01:14:19.640 --> 01:14:22.438
...if we go into the bull ride
and be the second or third place.

1111
01:14:22.600 --> 01:14:23.953
- But we're in last right now.
- Yeah.

1112
01:14:24.120 --> 01:14:26.156
We're only 20 points away
from being in second.

1113
01:14:26.320 --> 01:14:29.551
If we win every event from here on.
the money is ours.

1114
01:14:29.720 --> 01:14:32.996
Come on now. put it in together!
Everybody! Durango on three!

1115
01:14:33.160 --> 01:14:36.277
One. two. three. Durango!

1116
01:14:37.000 --> 01:14:38.035
Hey. guys!

1117
01:14:38.960 --> 01:14:41.235
I just wanted
to give you a little heads up.

1118
01:14:41.400 --> 01:14:44.551
I heard the Silver Spurs are planning
on having veal to celebrate.

1119
01:14:44.720 --> 01:14:46.472
- What's veal?
- You are. man.

1120
01:15:06.400 --> 01:15:10.154
Forget that!
I'm nobody's main course. pal!

1121
01:15:11.480 --> 01:15:12.959
One down. two to go.

1122
01:15:16.480 --> 01:15:18.516
- Hey!
- Hey! You talk to the steer?

1123
01:15:19.400 --> 01:15:22.551
No. but I have a plan.
I want you to close your eyes.

1124
01:15:23.720 --> 01:15:24.789
Yeah. alright.

1125
01:15:25.480 --> 01:15:27.391
And I want you to picture donuts.

1126
01:15:27.920 --> 01:15:31.629
But not just any donuts.
Glazed donuts.

1127
01:15:32.840 --> 01:15:35.035
And not just any glazed donuts.

1128
01:15:35.360 --> 01:15:39.399
Fresh. hot out of the oven
glazed donuts.

1129
01:15:39.800 --> 01:15:42.917
- Now you are speaking my language.
- And most importantly...

1130
01:15:43.320 --> 01:15:45.880
...I want you to picture
those hot glazed donuts...

1131
01:15:46.240 --> 01:15:48.435
...on the horns of this steer.

1132
01:15:51.960 --> 01:15:53.075
Okay. let me at him!

1133
01:15:53.880 --> 01:15:55.313
Come here. donuts!
I'll catch you!

1134
01:16:00.240 --> 01:16:03.789
Ladies and gentlemen.
looks like we have a new record!

1135
01:16:04.040 --> 01:16:06.952
3.4 seconds!

1136
01:16:07.240 --> 01:16:11.677
Let's give it up for Clayton Taylor!

1137
01:16:12.960 --> 01:16:15.918
Note to self: Definitely
do not steal their donuts either.

1138
01:16:18.120 --> 01:16:20.350
Looks like it's time
for some barrel racing!

1139
01:16:20.520 --> 01:16:22.192
Give our teams a round of applause...

1140
01:16:22.360 --> 01:16:24.999
...as they enter the ring
in order of the standings.

1141
01:16:29.400 --> 01:16:30.355
Come on!

1142
01:16:34.360 --> 01:16:35.679
Hey. what's the matter?

1143
01:16:35.920 --> 01:16:38.639
It's my hand.
I think I busted it up.

1144
01:16:39.560 --> 01:16:41.437
Okay. just let me take a look at it.

1145
01:16:41.600 --> 01:16:43.431
Just be really careful
because it really hurts.

1146
01:16:45.080 --> 01:16:48.072
Ow. Maya. God! That really hurts!

1147
01:16:48.240 --> 01:16:52.279
- Can she ride?
- No. It's definitely broken.

1148
01:16:54.600 --> 01:16:57.558
It's okay. guys. It's over. though.

1149
01:16:59.880 --> 01:17:00.869
I'm sorry.

1150
01:17:03.920 --> 01:17:04.989
No. it's not.

1151
01:17:06.440 --> 01:17:07.668
Not yet. anyway.

1152
01:17:09.880 --> 01:17:12.633
- Maya. what are you doing?
- Yeah. what are you doing?

1153
01:17:12.720 --> 01:17:14.278
- Welcome aboard.
- Thanks.

1154
01:17:14.720 --> 01:17:16.073
What does it look like I'm doing?

1155
01:17:16.240 --> 01:17:17.832
You haven't even trained
for this event!

1156
01:17:18.000 --> 01:17:20.639
You said the hardest part
of barrel racing is the ground...

1157
01:17:20.960 --> 01:17:22.712
...so I just won't hit it.

1158
01:17:25.200 --> 01:17:26.155
Alright.

1159
01:17:26.880 --> 01:17:28.996
I'll go tell them
we have another rider.

1160
01:17:32.080 --> 01:17:34.833
Just hold on tight
and I'll take care of the rest.

1161
01:17:35.120 --> 01:17:38.032
Sounds like a plan.
Come on. let's go.

1162
01:17:38.280 --> 01:17:41.272
Pay attention. and don't fall off.
or you'll be dead.

1163
01:17:41.440 --> 01:17:42.714
What? You're just joking. right?

1164
01:17:43.040 --> 01:17:46.476
Ladies and gentlemen.
Brooklyn Webster has a broken hand...

1165
01:17:46.640 --> 01:17:48.232
- Mom?!
- Maya!

1166
01:17:49.320 --> 01:17:51.151
You don't have to do this. you know.

1167
01:17:51.480 --> 01:17:54.358
Yes. I do. If it was me.
you would have done the same thing.

1168
01:17:54.520 --> 01:17:57.193
I've got to apologize for being
such a jerk to you all summer.

1169
01:17:57.360 --> 01:18:01.512
I'm not good at getting along
with people when I'm jealous of them.

1170
01:18:02.840 --> 01:18:05.673
I want you to go out there.
I want you to make us proud.

1171
01:18:06.800 --> 01:18:07.755
I got you.

1172
01:18:07.920 --> 01:18:10.229
The time to beat is 16 seconds.

1173
01:18:10.480 --> 01:18:13.438
You were just kidding about
the whole "die" thing. right?

1174
01:18:14.080 --> 01:18:15.832
Hello? Oh. no!

1175
01:18:19.680 --> 01:18:20.954
Come on. let's go!

1176
01:18:26.400 --> 01:18:27.389
Come on. Butch!

1177
01:18:30.920 --> 01:18:33.878
Okay. make it happen!
You can do this!

1178
01:18:36.680 --> 01:18:41.356
15.8 seconds for Maya Dolittle!

1179
01:18:42.440 --> 01:18:45.716
Oh my!
What a comeback for the Durangos!

1180
01:18:45.880 --> 01:18:49.156
With that win they move into second
place in the overall standing...

1181
01:18:49.320 --> 01:18:50.753
...with just one event to go.

1182
01:18:50.920 --> 01:18:53.673
That's right. folks.
it's time for the bull ride!

1183
01:19:13.600 --> 01:19:16.512
- Relax. son.
- Yeah. tell that to him.

1184
01:19:17.920 --> 01:19:19.273
Don't worry. I will.

1185
01:19:19.440 --> 01:19:23.592
No. Maya. look. This is something
that I need to do on my own. Okay?

1186
01:19:33.480 --> 01:19:34.469
Ride him!

1187
01:19:35.240 --> 01:19:37.515
6 seconds. folks. Not bad!

1188
01:19:38.680 --> 01:19:43.037
And now the highly anticipated
comeback ride of Bo Jones!

1189
01:19:43.760 --> 01:19:47.309
This is for the whole enchilada. folks!
Talk about pressure!

1190
01:19:47.520 --> 01:19:49.715
Prepare to meet your maker.

1191
01:19:50.440 --> 01:19:52.829
Are you sure
you don't want me to talk to him?

1192
01:19:53.640 --> 01:19:54.993
Why? Did he say something?

1193
01:19:55.200 --> 01:19:56.349
Nothing you wanna hear.

1194
01:19:58.040 --> 01:19:59.996
I'm not gonna lie to you again.

1195
01:20:00.640 --> 01:20:04.189
He said: "Prepare to meet your maker".
but he said it in a nice way.

1196
01:20:05.400 --> 01:20:07.311
Great! I feel better now!

1197
01:20:17.640 --> 01:20:18.595
Stay on!

1198
01:20:28.080 --> 01:20:29.877
Yeah! Stay on!

1199
01:20:35.120 --> 01:20:36.075
Bo!

1200
01:20:39.720 --> 01:20:43.713
Get up. son! Get up. Bo!

1201
01:20:45.160 --> 01:20:46.275
Hey. guys. he's gone!

1202
01:20:47.800 --> 01:20:49.028
Get up. son!

1203
01:20:49.920 --> 01:20:53.435
- Bo! Wake up. Bo! Come on. son.
- Is he alright?

1204
01:20:55.440 --> 01:20:56.509
Wake up. son!

1205
01:20:59.200 --> 01:21:04.354
It's official. folks: Bo Jones managed
to stay on for the full 8 seconds!

1206
01:21:04.520 --> 01:21:05.475
You hear that. Bo?

1207
01:21:07.200 --> 01:21:08.189
Son?

1208
01:21:09.920 --> 01:21:11.672
Not bad for a has-been. huh?

1209
01:21:19.960 --> 01:21:26.718
That means the winner of the 50.000
dollar first prize is Jud Jones!

1210
01:21:31.880 --> 01:21:33.313
I want to see a replay.

1211
01:21:49.680 --> 01:21:52.956
Boy. it just wouldn't be our style
to go out any other way. would it?

1212
01:21:53.600 --> 01:21:56.797
I want to hear it on three!
Durango on three!

1213
01:21:57.080 --> 01:22:00.914
One. two. three. Durango!

1214
01:22:08.120 --> 01:22:11.874
Ladies. I'll be back in a second. I'm just
going to step out for some fresh air.

1215
01:22:12.040 --> 01:22:13.553
I've still got it...

1216
01:22:15.840 --> 01:22:18.991
- So. Bo...
- Yes! - Where are we going?

1217
01:22:19.240 --> 01:22:21.913
It wouldn't be a surprise if I told you
where we were going.

1218
01:22:22.200 --> 01:22:25.317
I just wanted to thank you properly
for helping us save the ranch.

1219
01:22:25.480 --> 01:22:26.469
You're welcome.

1220
01:22:27.560 --> 01:22:29.039
One second. sweetie...

1221
01:22:32.520 --> 01:22:33.475
Thank you.

1222
01:22:46.440 --> 01:22:47.429
Wait...

1223
01:22:54.200 --> 01:22:55.394
You're welcome.

1224
01:22:57.640 --> 01:23:00.916
Did I ever tell you I've got a lot
of other things to thank you for?

1225
01:23:02.000 --> 01:23:03.069
Come on!

1226
01:23:05.280 --> 01:23:06.998
Wait! Where is everybody anyway?

1227
01:23:14.720 --> 01:23:16.517
Surprise!

1228
01:23:21.800 --> 01:23:25.395
Oh. my God! It's my birthday party.
I completely forgot!

1229
01:23:25.680 --> 01:23:28.353
Okay. who are you
and what have you done with Maya?

1230
01:23:29.000 --> 01:23:32.629
- Happy birthday. girl!
- Oh. thank you so much.

1231
01:23:32.920 --> 01:23:34.797
- Happy birthday!
- Thank you.

1232
01:23:35.800 --> 01:23:38.075
- Happy birthday!
- Thank you!

1233
01:23:39.640 --> 01:23:43.474
- Oh. Mommy! Thank you so much!
- Happy birthday!

1234
01:23:44.640 --> 01:23:47.950
I didn't do it all myself.
I had a little help from your friends.

1235
01:23:50.480 --> 01:23:53.278
Oh my gosh.
this is way better than any boat!

1236
01:23:53.440 --> 01:23:55.032
- I know. right!
- I missed you!

1237
01:23:55.800 --> 01:23:59.554
As soon as you two are done shrieking.
some folks would like a word with you.

1238
01:24:00.120 --> 01:24:01.348
Wait. I'll be right back.

1239
01:24:02.960 --> 01:24:06.714
- You know you look the same
as you did when you were 16? - Thanks!

1240
01:24:07.960 --> 01:24:10.110
And thanks for taking care
of my little girl.

1241
01:24:10.280 --> 01:24:13.352
It's kind of funny: She's the one
that's been taking care of us.

1242
01:24:13.920 --> 01:24:14.875
Hey!

1243
01:24:15.200 --> 01:24:18.670
Maya. for what you did.
this is our way of saying thanks.

1244
01:24:18.840 --> 01:24:20.990
We'd have gotten you a gift
but we're broke!

1245
01:24:21.160 --> 01:24:24.470
I should be thanking you. guys!
We couldn't have done it without you!

1246
01:24:24.640 --> 01:24:28.428
Nah. come on. Go on.
Enjoy your party. You deserve it!

1247
01:24:28.600 --> 01:24:31.068
- Alright. I'll see you guys later.
- Bye. Maya.

1248
01:24:31.240 --> 01:24:33.356
Hey. Maya.
thanks for helping me find my Mojo!

1249
01:24:44.200 --> 01:24:45.519
Tell me something I don't know!

1250
01:25:12.160 --> 01:25:13.639
And so our story ends.

1251
01:25:14.080 --> 01:25:17.993
Not really. You see. Bo is up to see
Maya every weekend from Stanford.

1252
01:25:18.320 --> 01:25:21.039
Brooklyn and Maya talk every day.
Go figure. huh?

1253
01:25:21.320 --> 01:25:24.312
Tyler's coming back to Durango
next year to teach roping.

1254
01:25:24.520 --> 01:25:27.114
And Clayton...
Iost his baby fat...

1255
01:25:27.280 --> 01:25:29.748
...and he's now considered
quite the catch with the ladies.

1256
01:25:30.040 --> 01:25:32.429
But the important thing
is that Maya's doing great...

1257
01:25:32.600 --> 01:25:36.275
...happy to be exactly who she is:
A Dolittle.

1258
01:25:38.160 --> 01:25:41.197
As for me. I'm still
the old dog I've always been.

1259
01:25:41.760 --> 01:25:43.557
Only now I've got a country gal...

1260
01:25:43.720 --> 01:25:46.439
...who I like to visit
when the city babes get me down.

1261
01:25:46.600 --> 01:25:50.070
City babes? You and me are going
to have talk. Lucky Dolittle.

1262
01:25:50.280 --> 01:25:53.636
Women... Can't live with them.
can't live without them!

1263
01:26:00.280 --> 01:26:53.636
THE END
Subtitles by: Reklame11
